   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Turn £10,000 into £1.48 million in one year. That is the aspirational ceiling — the mathematical upper bound if every
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: single trading day produces a 2% gain. Nobody hits 100% of targets. The realistic range, depending on win rate and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: average reward, is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £102,000 to £338,000 in Year 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Even the conservative end represents a 10x return, tax-free.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How It Works
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Every Sunday night
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , the system audits 5,000+ stocks and funds listed worldwide. It filters them
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: down to the 300 most tradeable instruments — the ones with enough daily volume, tight enough
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spreads, and large enough price swings to clear a 2% profit hurdle.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Every 60 seconds during London market hours (08:00–16:30 UK)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , the engine scans all 300
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: candidates and scores them in real time. It is looking for exactly one thing: the single best trade of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the day — long (betting the price goes up) or short (betting it goes down).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If a 3x or 5x leveraged fund exists on the London Stock Exchange
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that tracks the winning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: candidate, the system uses it. A 3x fund turns a 1% move in the underlying stock into a 3% move.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: These funds trade inside a UK ISA, so every penny of profit is tax-free.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When the trade hits +6% (the daily target)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , the system locks in 33% of the position as guaranteed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: profit. The remaining 67% rides with no ceiling — capturing 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fat tail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  moves where a stock runs 10%,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 15%, or more in a single session. This asymmetry is the engine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s core mathematical edge.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After every trade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , a self-learning AI meta-model reviews what happened — the entry signal, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: market regime, the exit timing — and adjusts its confidence weights. Separately, 10 independent risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: controls (the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gauntlet
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) must unanimously agree before any trade fires. If even one says no, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system sits in cash.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Tax Shield
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Every trade executes inside a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UK Individual Savings Account (ISA)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Under current HMRC rules:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Capital gains tax: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (normally 20% on gains above the annual allowance)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dividend tax: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No annual reporting obligation on ISA gains
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is the single largest structural edge in the system. A taxable account compounding at 2% daily loses
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: approximately 0.4% per day to deferred tax drag (assuming periodic crystallisation). Over 252 trading days, the ISA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wrapper alone accounts for a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.7x cumulative advantage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  versus an equivalent taxable General Investment Account.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Math
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Scenario | Daily Return | Formula | Year 1 Outcome |
