   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = Win Rate. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = Reward-to-Risk ratio (average win / average loss).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Moderate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  scenario incorporates Gemini
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Monte Carlo simulation 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 10,000 paths with 60% win rate,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.5R reward ratio, 40bps round-trip spread cost, and daily variance drawn from empirical leveraged ETP return
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: distributions. The geometric mean daily return across all surviving paths (i.e., those not hitting the 25% max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drawdown kill switch) was 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.14%/day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , yielding approximately £177,000 at year-end.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The conservative scenario uses the Kelly-adjusted fractional position sizing described in Section 4 (forthcoming),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which deliberately under-bets to survive the left tail.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 1: THE UNIVERSE REGISTRAR — High-Velocity Liquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Filtration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.0 Problem Statement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A compounding engine is only as good as the opportunity set it scans. The current NZT-48 implementation operates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on a critically narrow universe:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Component | Current State | Limitation |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | ISA Universe | 12 core ETPs, hardcoded in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uk_isa/isa_universe.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | No dynamic graduation. Misses new LSE listings. Cannot adapt to liquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime changes. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Bot B Universe | 18 US equities, hardcoded in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config/settings.yaml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Arbitrary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: selection. No capacity-weighted ranking. No spread-adjusted filtering. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | LSE Registry | 52 products auto-scraped
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: daily via 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uk_isa/lse_registry.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Scrape logic is solid, but no Amihud sieve, no ASER filter, no DSR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: graduation gate. Products enter the universe without proving statistical edge. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Broader Market | None | No Russell
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3000 scanning. No FTSE 350 scanning. No sector rotation signal from breadth data. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The result: on any given day, the engine chooses from at most 30 instruments. On a day where none of the 12 ISA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETPs exhibit 2%-reachable setups, the engine sits idle — forfeiting the compounding day entirely. Every missed day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: costs approximately 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £200 at £10K equity, scaling to £29,700 at £1.48M equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (2% of current NAV).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Target state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : a two-tier universe of 500–1,000 instruments, dynamically maintained, with every ticker earning its
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: place through three independent statistical filters.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.1 Architecture: Two-Tier Universe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tier 1: 
