   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Median bid-ask spread 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0.45% 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R1: tightened from 0.60% after spread cost sensitivity analysis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Amihud illiquidity score (leverage-adjusted) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0.005 per heat size (see Section 1.2.1)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For LSE ETPs: listed on LSE Main Market or ETF segment, ISA-eligible (see Section 1.2.4)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scan Frequency:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Every 60 seconds during market hours (08:00–16:30 UK for LSE, 14:30–21:00 UK for US). This is the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: existing 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: continuous_scan
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  cadence — no change required.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tier 2: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Radar
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 200–500 Pre-Filtered Tickers, Scanned Every 30 Minutes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Radar tier is the feeder pool. These are instruments that passed the initial Sunday-night liquidity screen but have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not yet demonstrated sufficient edge to warrant 60-second scanning. The purpose of Radar is twofold: (a) detect
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: breakout candidates early enough to promote them to Core before the move is over, and (b) provide sector breadth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data for the macro regime model.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Composition:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Source | Count | Refresh Cadence |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Russell 3000 subset (market cap > $500M, ADV > $10M/day) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 100–300 | Sunday 22:00 UTC full rebuild + daily 06:00 UTC delta |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | FTSE 350 liquid constituents not already in Core |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 50–100 | Sunday 22:00 UTC full rebuild + daily 06:00 UTC delta |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Recently demoted from Core (90-day cool-off) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 10–50 | Continuous |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Total
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 200–500
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scan Frequency:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Every 30 minutes during market hours. The scan is lightweight: fetch 5-minute OHLCV bars (not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1-minute), compute RVOL Z-Score, and flag anomalies. Only tickers with RVOL Z > 2.0 trigger a full predictive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scoring pass.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Critical Implementation Constraint — yfinance Rate Limits
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: C
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: yfinance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s batch download endpoint (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: yf.download()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) accepts up to ~250 tickers per call for 1-minute data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: before encountering HTTP 429 throttling. For 5-minute data, the effective limit is higher (~500) but unreliable under
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: load.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Solution:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Split Radar scans into batches of 50 tickers with 2-second inter-batch delay. A 500-ticker Radar scan at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 50/batch = 10 batches = ~25 seconds total including processing. This fits comfortably within the 30-minute scan
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: window.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Pseudocode for Radar batch scanner
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BATCH_SIZE = 50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: INTER_BATCH_DELAY = 2.0  # seconds
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for i in range(0, len(radar_tickers), BATCH_SIZE):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     batch = radar_tickers[i:i+BATCH_SIZE]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     data = yf.download(batch, period="5d", interval="5m",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: group_by="ticker")
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     anomalies = detect_rvol_anomalies(data, z_threshold=2.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     promoted += [t for t in anomalies if passes_core_filters(t)]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     await asyncio.sleep(INTER_BATCH_DELAY)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What was REMOVED from prior Aegis drafts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: C
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~~3,000-ticker Radar scanning every 30 minutes via yfinance 1-minute data~~. This was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computationally infeasible and would trigger rate limits within 2 batches. Replaced with the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pre-filtered 200–500 hot-ticker approach refreshed Sunday + daily 06:00 delta.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~~Real-time WebSocket feeds for Radar tickers~~. Cost-prohibitive at this equity level. WebSocket
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: feeds from LSE SETS cost £500+/month. Reserved for >£100K equity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.2 The Three Filters
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Every ticker — whether entering Core from Radar, or entering Radar from the Sunday full-universe scan — must pass three
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: independent statistical filters in sequence. Failure at any stage is an immediate PURGE (removal from the tier). The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: filters are ordered from cheapest to most expensive computationally.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.2.1 Filter 1: Amihud-Lambda Capacity Sieve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic Foundation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Amihud (2002), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Illiquidity and Stock Returns: Cross-Section and Time-Series Effects,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Journal of Financial Markets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 5(1), 31–56. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Extension for Leveraged ETPs:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Avellaneda 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang (2010), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Path-Dependence of Leveraged ETF Returns,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SIAM Journal on Financial Mathematics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 1(1), 586–603. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — establishes that leveraged ETPs exhibit convex
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: delta-hedging costs that scale super-linearly with leverage ratio.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Problem:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A ticker may show a 5% daily range, but if our position size moves the market by 50bps on entry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: alone, the effective range is 4.5% — potentially below the profit threshold. Leveraged ETPs compound this problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because the fund
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s own delta-hedging activity consumes liquidity, particularly near the close.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Formula:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ILLIQ_i = (1/D) × Σ_{d=1}^{D} (|r_d| / V_d) × L^α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Symbol | Definition | Source |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ILLIQ_i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Amihud illiquidity ratio for ticker 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , leverage-adjusted |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Amihud (2002) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: D
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Number of trading days in lookback window (default: 20) | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: r_d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Daily return on day 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: V_d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Daily dollar (or sterling) volume on day 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Leverage ratio of the ETP (1 for unleveraged, 3 for 3x, 5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for 5x) | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Leverage convexity exponent | Calibrated per product class |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Leverage Exponent Calibration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Product Class | α | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Unleveraged equities | 1.0 | No delta-hedging. Standard Amihud. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 2x
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leveraged ETPs | 1.25 | Modest delta-hedging, typically daily rebalance. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 3x leveraged ETPs | 1.5 | Significant daily
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rebalance. Empirically validated on QQQ3.L, 3LUS.L. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 5x leveraged ETPs | 2.0 | Convex delta-hedging costs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dominate. QQQ5.L shows 2.1x the illiquidity impact of QQQ3.L at equivalent notional. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5x
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: products show more convex delta-hedging; α=2.0 is conservative.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Time-of-Day Volume Adjustment
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R1 proposed, G-R2 ACCEPT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Intraday volume follows a well-documented U-shaped pattern (Admati 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Pfleiderer, 1988 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; Biais, Hillion 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spatt, 1995 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ). Using discrete volume buckets (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: morning = 1.3x, midday = 0.7x, close = 1.4x
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) creates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discontinuities that can cause filter flip-flopping at bucket boundaries.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Solution:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sinusoidal volume adjustment model:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: V_adj(t) = V_raw(t) / f(t)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f(t) = 1.25 - 0.25 × cos(2π(t - 9) / 8.5)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is hours since midnight (e.g., 9.0 = 09:00, 16.5 = 16:30). This produces:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Time | f(t) | Interpretation |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 09:00 (open) | 1.50 | Volume 50% above daily average — deflate to normalise |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 12:45 (midday) | 1.00 | Volume at daily average — no adjustment |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 16:30 (close) | 1.43 | Volume 43% above daily
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: average — deflate to normalise |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The sinusoidal model 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: smooth U-shape better than discrete steps
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  eliminates the bucket-boundary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discontinuity problem while remaining computationally trivial (single cosine evaluation per timestamp).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Purge Criterion:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: IF (heat_size_sterling × ILLIQ_i) > 0.005:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     PURGE ticker from universe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     LOG: "Amihud purge: {ticker}, ILLIQ={ILLIQ_i:.6f},
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: impact={impact:.4f}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heat_size_sterling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is the maximum position size in GBP for the current equity level (determined by
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the Kelly-fractional sizer in Section 4). The 0.005 threshold means: our maximum position must not move the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: market by more than 50 basis points on entry. This is conservative — institutional desks typically allow 10–20bps — but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: appropriate for leveraged products where slippage compounds through the leverage ratio.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Edge Case Handling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: C
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: V_d = 0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for any day in the lookback (e.g., bank holiday, ticker halted), exclude that day from
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the average. Do NOT interpolate volume — zero-volume days are informative (they indicate illiquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If fewer than 10 valid trading days exist in the 20-day lookback, the ticker is automatically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PURGED (insufficient data for reliable ILLIQ estimation).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For newly listed ETPs (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  20 trading days of history), use a conservative prior: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ILLIQ_prior =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2 × median(ILLIQ across all tickers in same leverage class)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . This ticker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enters Radar, not Core, until 20 days of data accumulate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.2.2 Filter 2: ASER — ADR-to-Spread Efficiency Ratio
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Concept Origin:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Proprietary metric. No direct academic citation, but grounded in the market microstructure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: literature on effective spreads and their impact on short-horizon strategy profitability (Hasbrouck, 2009 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trading Costs and Returns for U.S. Equities: Estimating Effective Costs from Daily Data,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Journal of Finance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 64(3), 1445–1477).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Problem:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A ticker with a 4% average daily range and a 1.5% bid-ask spread has an 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: effective
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  tradeable range of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only 2.5% — and that is before accounting for the spread cost on both entry AND exit. The true round-trip cost is:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Effective_range = ADR - (2 × median_spread) - execution_slippage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For a 2% daily target, this means any ticker with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ADR < 2% + 2 × spread + slippage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is mathematically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: incapable of delivering the target return.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Formula:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ASER_i = ADR_20d(i) / median_spread_20d(i)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Symbol | Definition |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ADR_20d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Average Daily Range over trailing 20 trading days: mean of 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (High_d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Low_d) / Close_d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: median_spread_20d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Median quoted bid-ask spread at 5-minute intervals over
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trailing 20 trading days, expressed as percentage of mid-price |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pass Criteria:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PASS if:  ADR_20d > 2.9%  AND  median_spread_20d < 0.45%  AND  ASER
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: > 6.4
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The ADR threshold of 2.9% 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: C
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  provides a 90bps buffer above the 2% target to absorb spread costs and slippage.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The spread threshold of 0.45% 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R1: tightened from 0.60%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  ensures round-trip spread cost stays below 90bps. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ASER floor of 6.4 (= 2.9 / 0.45) is implied by the joint thresholds but is checked independently as a sanity gate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Super-Fuel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Classification:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tickers passing ASER with extreme scores are flagged as 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Super-Fuel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — instruments where spread friction is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: negligible relative to available range:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | ASER Score | Classification | Example (current universe) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | > 15.0 | Super-Fuel Elite | QQQ3.L (ADR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~7.5%, spread ~0.35%) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 10.0–15.0 | Super-Fuel | 3LUS.L (ADR ~6.2%, spread ~0.42%) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 6.4–10.0 | Core-Eligible |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MU2.L (ADR ~3.8%, spread ~0.40%) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6.4 | PURGE | — |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Super-Fuel tickers receive a 1.15x confidence multiplier in the predictive scoring model (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uk_isa/predictive_scoring.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ), reflecting their superior execution characteristics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation Note
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: C
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The existing 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uk_isa/lse_registry.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  already scrapes LSE product pages and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extracts spread data. The ASER calculation should be added as a new column in the registry DataFrame, computed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: during the daily 06:00 UTC refresh. No new data source is required — only a new derived metric.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.2.3 Filter 3: Bayesian DSR Graduation Gate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic Foundation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Bailey 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Lopez de Prado (2014), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Deflated Sharpe Ratio: Correcting for Selection Bias,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Backtest Overfitting, and the Non-Normality of Returns,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Journal of Portfolio Management
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 40(5),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 94–107. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
