   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Harvey, Liu 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhu (2016), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ...and the Cross-Section of Expected Returns,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Review of Financial
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Studies
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 29(1), 5–68. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — establishes the t-stat ≥ 3.0 threshold for statistical significance under multiple
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: testing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Problem:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Adding a ticker to the Core universe is implicitly a claim that 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this instrument contributes positive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expected value to the strategy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That claim must survive multiple-testing correction. If we test 500 tickers and select
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the 50 with the highest raw Sharpe ratios, we are virtually guaranteed to select noise traders alongside genuine alpha
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sources (the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: p-hacking
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  problem applied to universe construction).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Deflated Sharpe Ratio (DSR):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The DSR adjusts the observed Sharpe ratio for:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Multiple testing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — the more tickers we evaluate, the higher the bar each must clear
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Non-normality
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — leveraged ETP returns exhibit significant skewness and excess kurtosis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sample length
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — short track records are penalised
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR_adj = DSR_observed / √(E[max(z_1, z_2, ..., z_k)])
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Symbol | Definition |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR_observed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Standard Sharpe ratio of the ticker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s contribution to portfolio
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: returns |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: k
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Number of tickers evaluated (the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trial count
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E[max(z_k)]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Expected maximum of k
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: independent standard normal draws ≈ √(2 × ln(k)) for large k (Bonferroni-style adjustment) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR_adj
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | The deflated
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (corrected) Sharpe ratio |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For k = 500 tickers: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E[max(z_500)] ≈ √(2 × ln(500)) ≈ 3.52
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . This means a ticker must exhibit a raw Sharpe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ratio of approximately 3.52 × 1.5 = 5.28 to graduate with DSR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: adj > 1.5.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Multiple testing correction is essential when expanding from 30 to 500 tickers. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Bonferroni-style adjustment via DSR is conservative but appropriate for a system where false positives directly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: translate to capital loss.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Bayesian Prior Specification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 Q6 — addressed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rather than a pure frequentist DSR, we embed the graduation decision in a Bayesian framework to incorporate prior
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beliefs about the distribution of genuine alpha:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Prior on edge (daily excess return):  μ_edge ~ Normal(0, 0.5%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Prior on volatility:                  σ_edge ~ Inv-Gamma(3, 0.1)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale for prior choice:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: μ_edge ~ Normal(0, 0.5%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Centered at zero (no prior belief that any arbitrary ticker has
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: positive edge). Standard deviation of 0.5% reflects that leveraged ETPs can exhibit genuine daily
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: edges in the range of -1% to +1% due to structural features (volatility decay, momentum premium,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leverage rebalancing flows).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: σ_edge ~ Inv-Gamma(3, 0.1)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Weakly informative prior on return volatility. Shape
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: parameter 3 ensures finite variance; scale parameter 0.1 places the prior mode at 5% annualised
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: volatility, which is deliberately low (most leveraged ETPs exhibit 30–80% annualised vol). This allows
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the data to dominate quickly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Graduation Criterion:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GRADUATE to Core if:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     P(Sharpe_annual > 1.5 | observed_returns, prior) > 0.98
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     AND n_trades >= 30
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     AND n_volatility_regimes >= 2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n_volatility_regimes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is counted by the VIX regime classifier in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uk_isa/volatility_regime.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : a ticker must have been traded in at least two of {Low-Vol, Normal,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: High-Vol, Crisis} regimes to demonstrate robustness.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Demotion Criterion:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DEMOTE from Core to Radar if:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     P(Sharpe_annual > 0.5 | observed_returns, prior) < 0.80
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     OR trailing_30d_ASER < 5.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     OR trailing_30d_Amihud_impact > 0.004
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Demotion triggers a 90-day cool-off in Radar. During cool-off, the ticker continues to accumulate trade data (paper
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trades only) and may re-graduate if the Bayesian posterior recovers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Connection to Existing Code
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: C
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The S16 strategy framework (referenced in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:38,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: strategies/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  directory) already
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: implements an A/B team rotation system where strategies are promoted and demoted based on rolling performance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The DSR Graduation Gate extends this concept from strategy-level to ticker-level. The posterior computation can be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: implemented via conjugate Normal-Inverse-Gamma updates (closed-form, no MCMC required), keeping
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computational cost trivial.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.2.4 ISA Eligibility Gate 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 NEW
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regulatory Foundation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  HMRC ISA Regulations, SI 1998/1870 as amended. Individual Savings Account
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Amendment No. 2) Regulations 2014 (SI 2014/1450). 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A — statutory instrument, not academic, but binding.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Problem:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Expanding from 30 to 500 tickers introduces instruments that may NOT be ISA-qualifying.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Executing a non-qualifying trade inside an ISA wrapper voids the tax-free status of the entire account — a catastrophic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outcome that would retroactively crystallise CGT on all prior gains.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ISA-Qualifying Criteria (simplified):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Shares
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  must be listed on a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recognised stock exchange
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (LSE Main Market, NYSE, NASDAQ, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~50 others per HMRC list).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETFs/ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  must be UCITS-compliant OR listed on a recognised exchange AND the investor must
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hold fewer than 10% of the fund.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ADRs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (American Depositary Receipts) for non-US companies: qualifying status depends on the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: underlying exchange listing. Many Russell 3000 ADRs for Chinese or emerging market companies
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are NOT ISA-eligible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OTC-traded instruments
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , pink sheet stocks, and instruments traded solely on MTFs (Multilateral
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trading Facilities) that are not HMRC-recognised: NOT eligible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # New module: uk_isa/isa_eligibility.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: class ISAEligibilityChecker:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Determines whether a given ticker is eligible for inclusion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     in a UK ISA wrapper per HMRC regulations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Data source: HMRC recognised stock exchanges list, cached
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weekly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Fallback: Conservative deny-list for ambiguous instruments.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     RECOGNISED_EXCHANGES = {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         'LSE', 'NYSE', 'NASDAQ', 'XETRA', 'EURONEXT',
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         'TSX', 'ASX', 'HKEX', 'TSE', 'SGX',
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         # ... full HMRC list (~50 exchanges)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def is_eligible(self, ticker: str, exchange: str,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     instrument_type: str) -> bool:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if exchange not in self.RECOGNISED_EXCHANGES:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return False
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if instrument_type == 'ADR':
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return self._check_adr_underlying(ticker)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if instrument_type in ('ETP', 'ETF'):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return self._check_ucits_or_exchange(ticker, exchange)
