   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.6 Risk Considerations for Universe Expansion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expanding from 30 to 500+ tickers introduces risks that must be explicitly managed:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Data Quality Degradation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: C
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : More tickers means more edge cases — stock splits, ticker changes, delistings,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: corporate actions. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: universe_fetcher.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  module must implement a data quality scorecard: each ticker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: receives a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data_quality_score
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (0–1) based on missing bars, zero-volume days, and price discontinuities.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tickers with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data_quality_score < 0.85
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  are automatically quarantined in Radar regardless of filter scores.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Overfitting via Selection Bias
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A: Harvey, Liu 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhu 2016
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The Bayesian DSR gate (Section 1.2.3) is the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: primary defence. However, an additional safeguard is required: the universe composition must be logged immutably
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (append-only SQLite table) with timestamps, so that any future backtest can reconstruct the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: actual
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  universe at any
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: historical point — not the survivorship-biased universe visible in hindsight.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Execution Capacity at Scale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : If the engine scales to £1M+ equity, the Amihud sieve parameters must be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re-calibrated. The current 0.005 impact threshold assumes £10K–£50K position sizes. At £500K positions, the threshold
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should tighten to 0.002. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amihud_sieve.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  module must accept 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: equity_level
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  as a dynamic input, not a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hardcoded constant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. Regulatory Change Risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : HMRC may modify ISA-qualifying criteria, recognised exchange lists, or annual
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: contribution limits (currently £20,000/year). The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: isa_eligibility.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  module includes a staleness alert, but the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operations playbook (Section 8, forthcoming) must include a quarterly manual review of HMRC guidance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: End of Section 1. Section 2 (Signal Intelligence Chain) continues in v13
