   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 1B -- Fatal Flaws (Pre-Launch CRO Audit)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Auditor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : AEGIS CRO (Chief Risk Officer)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Date
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 2026-03-04
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scope
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : All code-verified deficiencies in the production codebase and architectural deficiencies inherited from the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Aegis v10.0 plan document.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Each flaw is classified by Severity (CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM /
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LOW), pinpointed to file and line, and paired with a prescriptive fix. No flaw is theoretical -- every one was verified
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: against the live codebase.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART I: FATAL FLAWS IN CURRENT CODEBASE (12 Flaws,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code-Verified)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-01 | CRITICAL | Signal Queue Silently Drops Signals
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: main.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L1136
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: self._signal_queue: Queue = Queue(maxsize=50)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The signal queue is bounded at 50 entries. When the queue is full, new signals are silently dropped. There is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no overflow handler, no logging of dropped signals, and no priority mechanism. During high-volatility regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transitions -- precisely when S15 generates the most actionable signals -- the queue saturates first. The highest-value
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signals (S15 daily target candidates with peak reachability scores) compete for queue space with low-priority
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: informational signals and are discarded with no trace.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Missed S15 entries during the exact conditions that produce 2%+ moves. On a single high-volatility day,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this can cost the daily compounding target entirely. Over 252 trading days, even 5 missed optimal entries
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compounds to a significant equity shortfall versus the theoretical curve.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Replace with an unbounded 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: asyncio.PriorityQueue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Assign priority tiers: P0 = S15 daily target, P1 =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: active strategy signals, P2 = informational/monitoring. Add a counter metric for queue depth and emit a Telegram
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: alert if depth exceeds 100. Back-pressure should throttle low-priority signal generation, never drop high-priority
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signals.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-02 | CRITICAL | Regime Transition Instantly Flattens All Positions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: main.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L4500-4611 (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _handle_regime_transition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # SHOCK: Emergency flatten everything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: if new_regime == RegimeState.SHOCK:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ...
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # RISK_OFF: Flatten everything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: if new_regime == RegimeState.RISK_OFF:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ...
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # TRENDING_UP -> TRENDING_DOWN: Flatten all longs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: if prev in up_regimes and new_regime in down_regimes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ...
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Every regime transition triggers immediate position liquidation with zero confirmation delay. A single noisy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tick in the VIX feed, a momentary data glitch, or a transient macro signal misfire causes the system to flatten the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entire portfolio and lock in losses at the worst possible prices. The SHOCK, RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF, UP-to-DOWN, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOWN-to-UP transitions all execute market-order closes within the same scan cycle that detected the regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: change. There is no confirmation window, no second-tick validation, and no distinction between a genuine regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shift and sensor noise.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Whipsaw losses. A single false SHOCK classification flattens all positions at bid prices, then the regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reverts on the next scan cycle. The system has already crystallised losses and must re-enter at worse prices. During
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: paper trading, this manifests as unexplained drawdowns that do not correlate with actual market moves. In live
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trading with 3x/5x leverage, a single false flatten event on a full portfolio can exceed the daily loss budget.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Implement a 3-tick confirmation buffer for all regime transitions except SHOCK (which retains instant flatten
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but requires VIX > 40 AND credit spread blowout simultaneously, not either/or). For non-SHOCK transitions: the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: new regime must persist for 3 consecutive scan cycles (approximately 3 minutes at 60s intervals) before position
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: actions execute. During the confirmation window, tighten all stops to breakeven as a defensive measure. Log each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confirmation tick to the regime audit trail.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-03 | CRITICAL | No Portfolio-Level Correlation Brake
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: main.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L2441-2474 (Portfolio Risk Gate)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The portfolio risk gate at L2441-2474 checks concentration, directional exposure, and budget limits, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: performs no cross-position correlation analysis before admitting new trades. The S16 gauntlet (L4299-4313) has a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: per-strategy 0.80 correlation check, but this is S16-specific and does not apply to the primary S15 strategy or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mixed-strategy portfolios. Meanwhile, the ISA universe is heavily NASDAQ-correlated: QQQ3.L, NVD3.L,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3SEM.L, GPT3.L, TSL3.L, and TSM3.L all have pairwise correlations exceeding 0.85 with the NASDAQ-100. A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: portfolio holding 3+ of these instruments has an effective position count of approximately 1.2, not 3. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RealTimeCorrelationMatrix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (L769-770) exists but is only used for spike detection and S16 gating, not as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: an admission gate for all strategies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Concentration risk masquerading as diversification. A single NASDAQ downtick moves the entire
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: portfolio in lockstep. With 3x leverage on all positions, a 2% NASDAQ drop produces a 6% portfolio loss --
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exceeding any daily loss limit. The system believes it has 3 independent positions when it effectively has 1.2.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
