   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return True
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return False
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The kill switch persists via a file (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data/KILL_SWITCH
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) and a process-level flag. Once activated -- whether
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:39,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by drawdown circuit breaker, manual Telegram /kill command, or process signal -- there is no automatic recovery
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mechanism. The kill switch remains active across container restarts (the file persists on the Docker volume). A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weekend drawdown that triggers the kill switch on Friday at 21:00 will keep the system halted through Monday
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: open, missing the entire pre-market intelligence window and the first hours of trading. Manual intervention is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: required: either SSH into the EC2 instance and delete the file, or send a Telegram /unkill command (if one exists --
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it is not visible in the KillSwitch class).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Extended unplanned downtime. Every hour of missed trading during a trending regime is a missed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compounding opportunity. If the kill switch activates during a drawdown that subsequently recovers (e.g., a flash
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: crash reversal), the system misses the recovery entirely.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Implement automatic kill switch recovery at 06:00 UTC on trading days if the drawdown has recovered to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: within -1.0% of the session high-water mark. The recovery check should: (1) verify the current equity vs. the equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at kill-switch activation time, (2) require that the drawdown has reduced by at least 50% from its peak, (3) log the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: auto-recovery event to Telegram with full context, (4) set a CAUTION state for the first 30 minutes post-recovery
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (half-size only). Add a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: last_activated_at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  timestamp and 
