   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  field is included as an input feature to the LightGBM/XGBoost meta-model. This 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  value is the rule-based confidence score computed by the signal engine -- the very score that the ML
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model is supposed to evaluate and improve upon. Including it as an input creates a circular dependency: the model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: learns to parrot the rule-based confidence rather than discovering independent predictive features. During training, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  will dominate feature importance (it is directly correlated with the label by construction), masking
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: genuinely predictive features like 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rvol
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: atr_pct
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , and 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . The SHAP stability filter (L619-772) may eventually
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drop it if its rank drifts, but this is not guaranteed and depends on having 4+ training windows.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Inflated AUC during cross-validation (the model appears to perform well because it is partially memorising
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the label through its proxy). In production, the meta-label gate (L449-510) will veto or pass signals based largely on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a feature that is already baked into the signal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s own confidence score, providing no additional filtering power. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: De Prado (2018) meta-labelling framework specifically requires features that are independent of the primary model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: output.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Remove 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: feature_cols
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Replace it with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: raw_indicator_alignment_count
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  --
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the count of how many raw indicators (RSI, MACD, BB, VWAP, etc.) agree on direction, without any weighting or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scoring applied. This preserves the signal about indicator consensus without leaking the rule-based confidence score.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Retrain the model after the change and compare AUC with and without the leaked feature to quantify the inflation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-07 | HIGH | VIX Defaults to Zero on Fetch Failure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: main.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L4674-4685
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ms_data = self._market_structure.get_full_context()
