   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : When the market structure data fetch fails (network timeout, yfinance rate limit, API outage), the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  field
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: defaults to 0. A VIX of 0 is impossible in reality (the VIX has never been below 9.14 historically) and signals an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extremely calm market. The regime classifier will interpret VIX=0 as ultra-low volatility, selecting aggressive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position sizing and trending-up regime parameters. The cross-asset macro module (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/cross_asset_macro.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L86-111) has a separate fallback using 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _last_good_vix_spot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (default
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 20.0), but this is in the macro signal path, not the main market context builder. The two systems can diverge: the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: macro module thinks VIX is 20 while the regime classifier thinks VIX is 0.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : During a data outage that coincides with a genuine volatility spike (the most dangerous scenario), the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system will be maximally aggressive precisely when it should be most defensive. Position sizes will be too large,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime classification will be wrong, and the portfolio will be unhedged.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Replace the default-to-zero pattern with a cascading fallback: (1) use the last known good VIX value, (2) if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stale by more than 10 minutes, set regime to CAUTION and halve position sizes, (3) if stale by more than 30
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: minutes, set VIX to 30.0 (conservative assumption) and activate reduced-exposure mode. In all cases, compute the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fallback as 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max(last_known_vix, vix_20d_ma + 5.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to ensure the fallback is never lower than the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recent average. Add a staleness timestamp to the VIX data and expose it on the dashboard.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-08 | MEDIUM | 24/7 Scanning Wastes Compute on Weekends
