   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The main scan loop runs every 60 seconds, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. On weekends, bank holidays, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outside market hours (LSE closes at 16:30 UK, US pre-market starts at 09:00 UK), every scan cycle fetches stale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: price data, computes indicators on unchanged values, evaluates signals that cannot be acted upon, and logs repetitive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no change
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  entries. The only weekend check found in the codebase is a debug-level log suppression at L1567 for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: specific edge cases, not a comprehensive market calendar gate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Unnecessary EC2 compute cost (t3.small running hot 24/7), unnecessary yfinance API calls that count
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: toward rate limits, log pollution (thousands of identical 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no signal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  lines per weekend), and Redis write
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amplification on unchanged state. Over a year, this is approximately 2,500 hours of wasted compute (weekends +
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: holidays + overnight).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Implement a market calendar gate that restricts scanning to 06:00-22:00 UK time on LSE/NYSE trading days
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only. Use the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exchange_calendars
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  library (already a common Python package) to determine trading days for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: both LSE and NYSE. Outside the gate window, the scan loop should sleep for 15 minutes between heartbeat checks
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (container health only, no data fetching). Pre-market intelligence scans should wake up at 06:00 UK to prepare for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the LSE open at 08:00.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-09 | MEDIUM | Lunch RVOL Threshold 1.7 Too Restrictive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signal_engine/strategy_router.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L458-461
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "Lunch chop window: RVOL min 1.7 required (spec rule)",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: constraints={"tod_required": [TOD_LUNCH_CHOP], "min_rvol": 1.7},
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The lunch chop window (12:00-13:30 UK) requires a minimum RVOL of 1.7 for VWAP mean-reversion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signals. An RVOL of 1.7 means volume must be 70% above the 20-day average for that time-of-day bucket. During
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the lunch period, volume naturally drops by 30-50% from the morning session. Requiring 1.7x of an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: already-depressed baseline means the effective filter is closer to RVOL 2.5-3.0 relative to the full-day average. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: eliminates virtually all lunch-period signals, making the VWAP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MR strategy dormant during its intended operating
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: window.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The lunch chop strategy exists specifically to capture mean-reversion setups during low-volume
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: range-bound conditions. An excessively high RVOL filter contradicts the strategy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s premise -- if volume is 70%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: above normal during lunch, the market is not in a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lunch chop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  state, it is in an unusual-activity state better suited to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: momentum strategies. The filter self-defeats the strategy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Lower the lunch RVOL threshold to 1.3. This still requires above-average volume (ensuring liquidity for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: execution) without requiring the exceptional volume levels that invalidate the mean-reversion setup. Make the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold configurable via 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: settings.yaml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  so it can be tuned during paper trading without a code change.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-10 | MEDIUM | Daily Loss Halt Threshold Not Regime-Adaptive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk_officer/rules/drawdown.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L20-21, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/trading_discipline.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L60, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config/settings.yaml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L837-869
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _DAILY_LOSS_VETO_PCT       = 3.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _DAILY_LOSS_DOWNSIZE_PCT   = 1.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The daily loss halt is a fixed percentage across all regime states. In the drawdown rule, a 1.5% daily loss
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: triggers downsizing and 3.0% triggers a full veto. In 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: settings.yaml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , per-bot daily loss limits range from -0.75%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to -2.0%. None of these adapt to the current volatility regime. In a TRENDING regime, a 1.5% intraday drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is normal noise on 3x leveraged ETPs (a 0.5% underlying move produces a 1.5% ETP move). Triggering the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: downsize at -1.5% during a strong trend causes the system to reduce size precisely when it should be holding full
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: size for the 2% daily target. Conversely, in a HIGH
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VOL or SHOCK regime, a -1.5% drawdown may be the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beginning of a much larger move, and the system should halt earlier.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : In trending regimes: premature size reduction costs the daily compounding target. In volatile regimes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: insufficient protection allows losses to compound past the point where recovery is feasible within the session.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Make the daily loss halt regime-conditional: TRENDING = -2.5% (allow normal 3x noise), RANGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BOUND
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: = -1.5% (current default), HIGH
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VOL = -1.0% (tighter protection). SHOCK and RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF regimes should have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.0% tolerance (no new positions, existing positions managed by regime transition handler). Implement this in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk_officer/rules/drawdown.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  by accepting the current regime as a parameter to the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: check()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: method.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-11 | LOW | Kelly Cap at 0.75% Makes Computation Redundant
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bots/kelly_sizer.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L393, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: main.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L4011-4012
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: self.immutable_cap: float = kelly_cfg.get("cap", 0.0075)  # 0.75%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Half-Kelly with sample-size ramp, hard-capped at 0.75%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (immutable)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk_pct = self.kelly.get_risk_pct(ticker=signal.ticker) if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hasattr(self, 'kelly') and self.kelly else 0.0075
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The Kelly sizer computes a sophisticated Merton (1971) continuous-time fraction with jump-diffusion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extension (Merton 1976), Cornish-Fisher variance adjustment, leverage-dependent fractional Kelly (quarter for 3x,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fifth for 5x), sample-size ramp, and SHAP feature stability. After all this computation, the result is hard-capped at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.75%. For the typical ISA universe (3x-5x leverage), the jump-diffusion Kelly with quarter/fifth fractional scaling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: almost always produces a value well below 0.75%, making the cap redundant. When conditions are genuinely
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: favourable (strong edge, low vol, high sample size), the 0.75% cap prevents the system from sizing up, negating the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entire purpose of dynamic Kelly sizing. The cap converts a dynamic sizer into a fixed-fraction sizer with extra
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computation overhead.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : In RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF and SHOCK regimes, the Kelly fraction should be 0.0 (no position), but the cold-start
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fallback and the downstream code default to 0.75% regardless. The Kelly sizer computes a theoretically optimal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fraction that is never used at its computed value -- it is either capped down or defaulted up.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Make the Kelly cap regime-conditional. In RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF and SHOCK: 0.0 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (zero position, not 0.75% default).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In HIGH
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VOL: 0.25 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with a cap of 0.50%. In RANGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BOUND: 0.50 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with a cap of 0.75%. In
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TRENDING: 1.0 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with a cap of 1.25%. This allows the Kelly computation to actually influence sizing while
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maintaining an upper bound that scales with regime risk. The immutable 0.75% cap should become a constitutional
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maximum for the TRENDING regime, not a universal clamp.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F-12 | LOW | Macro Cache TTL 30 Minutes is Too Stale for VIX
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/cross_asset_macro.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L40
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _CACHE_SECONDS = 1800  # 30 minutes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The cross-asset macro module caches all macro signals (VIX term structure, DXY strength, credit spreads,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fear 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Greed, HMM regime) with a single 30-minute TTL. VIX can move 5-10 points in 30 minutes during a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: market stress event. A cached VIX value from 29 minutes ago may be 25% stale during the exact conditions when
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VIX accuracy matters most. Meanwhile, DXY, credit spreads, and Fear 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Greed are slow-moving indicators where
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 30-minute caching is perfectly adequate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : During rapid VIX spikes (the preamble to SHOCK regime), the system operates on stale VIX data for up to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 30 minutes. Regime classification, position sizing, and the VIX circuit breaker all consume the cached value. A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 30-minute lag on a VIX spike from 15 to 35 means the system runs aggressive sizing for half an hour into a market
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: crash.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Implement per-signal TTLs: VIX term structure = 5 minutes, DXY = 30 minutes, credit spread = 30 minutes,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fear 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Greed = 60 minutes, HMM = 30 minutes. Refactor 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _is_cache_fresh()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to accept a signal-specific TTL
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: parameter. For VIX specifically, consider a push-based update from the yfinance websocket (if available) or a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dedicated 60-second polling loop that updates only the VIX cache entry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART II: FATAL FLAWS IN AEGIS v10.0 PLAN (7 Flaws)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: These flaws are architectural or theoretical deficiencies in the original Aegis v10.0 plan document that, if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: implemented as specified, would produce incorrect behaviour or misleading performance expectations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A-01 | CRITICAL | 2% Daily Compounding Model Ignores Losing Days
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:40,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The foundational thesis states that 10,000 x (1.02)^252 = 1,485,757 (14,757% annualised). This calculation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: assumes a 2% gain on every single one of 252 trading days with zero losing days. This is not a simplification -- it is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the basis on which the target equity curve, drawdown budgets, and milestone timelines are computed. In reality,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: even a 60% win rate with a 2.5R reward-to-risk ratio and 40 basis points of execution spread (bid-ask + slippage on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3x ETPs) produces a geometric mean daily return of approximately 1.14%, not 2.0%. The gap between 1.14% and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.0% compounds catastrophically over 252 days: (1.0114)^252 = approximately 17.4x versus (1.02)^252 =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: approximately 148.6x -- an 8.5x overstatement of terminal wealth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : All downstream planning artifacts (capital deployment schedule, risk budgets, milestone dates, profit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: targets) are calibrated to a fantasy equity curve. When the system inevitably underperforms the 2% daily target,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: there is no framework for distinguishing 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system broken
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system performing correctly but below the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: impossible benchmark.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Operator confidence erodes, leading to parameter tampering and override-driven losses.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Model honestly using Monte Carlo simulation with realistic parameters: 60% WR, 2.0-2.5R average winner,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.0R average loser, 40bps round-trip friction, regime-dependent signal frequency (0-3 signals/day). The profit ladder
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Chandelier exit with 5-rung trailing stop) is the bridging mechanism that converts modest edge into compounding
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: returns -- document it as such. Replace the single-point 2% target with a distribution: P10 = 0.4%/day, P50 =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.9%/day, P90 = 1.8%/day. Set operational targets at P50, not P90.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A-02 | HIGH | Thomas 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang Beta Misapplied to Intraday Timeframe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The plan references Thomas 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s post-earnings announcement drift (PEAD) with beta = 0.40 as a basis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for earnings-related signal confidence adjustments. Thomas 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang (2002) measured PEAD over quarterly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: windows (60-90 trading days post-announcement). The system operates on intraday to 1-3 day holding periods. A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quarterly beta of 0.40 does not decompose linearly to intraday timeframes -- the drift is concentrated in the first 1-2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: days and then decays logarithmically. Applying a constant 0.40 beta across all holding periods overweights the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PEAD signal on day 2+ and underweights it on day 0.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Earnings-related signals on day 0 are under-weighted relative to their true edge, while signals on day 2+ are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: over-weighted. The system may hold earnings drift positions too long (expecting continued drift) when the edge has
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: already decayed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Replace the static beta = 0.40 with empirical pair-specific betas calibrated from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data/outcomes.jsonl
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each ticker, compute the realised drift coefficient at each holding period (0, 1, 2, 3 days post-earnings) from
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: historical outcomes. Use these empirical betas instead of the academic aggregate. If insufficient data exists for a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: specific ticker, shrink toward the cross-sectional median beta using Bayesian shrinkage.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A-03 | HIGH | RVOL Z-Score Threshold Too Selective for Universe Size
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The plan specifies RVOL Z > 3.0 as a minimum filter for signal generation. A Z-score of 3.0 corresponds to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the 99.87th percentile of the volume distribution. For a 12-ticker ISA universe scanned once per minute during a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.5-hour trading session, this produces approximately 390 scan-minutes per ticker per day. At Z > 3.0, only 0.13%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of scan-minutes pass the filter -- roughly 0.5 observations per ticker per day, or 6 across the entire universe. Most
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trading days will produce zero qualifying signals, making the 2% daily target unachievable by construction. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: filter is calibrated for a 3,000-ticker US equity universe (where 0.13% yields approximately 4 qualifying tickers per
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scan), not a 12-ticker concentrated universe.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The system starves itself of opportunities. On quiet days (40-60% of all trading days), zero signals pass the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RVOL gate, and the daily compounding target is missed by default. The no-signal-day protocol (A-06) becomes the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dominant operating mode rather than an exception handler.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Make the RVOL Z-score threshold adaptive by regime: TRENDING = 2.0 (more permissive, capture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: breakouts), RANGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BOUND = 2.5 (moderate, quality mean-reversion), HIGH
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VOL = 3.0 (strict, only act on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confirmed volume surges), SHOCK = 3.5 (maximum selectivity). Additionally, compute RVOL relative to the ticker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s own time-of-day volume profile, not the daily average, to avoid lunch-period penalisation (related to F-09).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A-04 | HIGH | Open-to-Close Velocity Ignores Overnight Gaps
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The plan uses Open-to-Close (O2C) velocity as a momentum signal, measuring intraday price displacement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: per unit time. For LSE-listed leveraged ETPs, overnight gaps (driven by US after-hours moves on the underlying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NASDAQ-100) routinely account for 50-80% of the total daily range. An ETP that gaps up 4% at the open and then
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trades flat for the rest of the day has an O2C velocity of approximately zero, despite a massive directional move
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: already being priced in. Conversely, a gap-down followed by an intraday reversal produces a positive O2C velocity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that masks the fact that the day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s net move is negative.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : O2C velocity generates false signals on gap days. A strong gap-up followed by flat trading produces a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: momentum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  reading that causes the system to skip the day, missing continuation moves. A gap-down with a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dead-cat bounce produces a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: positive momentum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  reading that triggers entries into positions that are net-negative
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for the day.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Compute a gap-to-range ratio for each ticker: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gap_ratio = abs(open - prev_close) / ADR_20
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gap_ratio > 0.50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (gap exceeds 50% of the 20-day average daily range), apply a -15 confidence penalty to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: any O2C-derived signal. Additionally, decompose total daily return into gap component and intraday component,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and use only the intraday component for O2C velocity calculations. This prevents gaps from polluting the velocity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A-05 | MEDIUM | Stranger Ticker Discount Does Not Decay
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The plan assigns a 0.5x confidence multiplier to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stranger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  tickers -- those with fewer than a minimum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: number of historical trades in the outcomes database. This discount is binary: below the threshold = 0.5x, above =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.0x. There is no decay function that gradually increases confidence as the sample size grows. A ticker with 49
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trades (one below threshold) receives 0.5x; a ticker with 50 trades (one above) jumps to 1.0x. This discontinuity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: creates perverse incentives: the system may avoid a ticker for months, then suddenly go full-size on its 50th trade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: without any gradual calibration period.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Position sizing exhibits a cliff-edge discontinuity at the stranger threshold. The first full-size trade on a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: newly-graduated ticker has no intermediate validation. If the first 49 trades were in a specific regime and trade 50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: occurs in a different regime, the system has no mechanism to detect this.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Replace the binary discount with Bayesian shrinkage toward the population mean. Define: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discount = 1 -
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lambda * exp(-n / n0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lambda = 0.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (maximum discount), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = number of historical trades for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this ticker, and 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n0 = 50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (half-life parameter). At n=0, discount = 0.5x. At n=50, discount = approximately 0.82x.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: At n=100, discount = approximately 0.93x. At n=200, discount = approximately 0.98x. Additionally, weight the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrinkage by the ticker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Drawdown Sharpe Ratio (DSR) to penalise tickers that have many trades but poor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk-adjusted performance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A-06 | MEDIUM | No 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No-Signal Day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Protocol
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The plan does not define what happens when the system reaches mid-afternoon without generating a single
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: qualifying signal. Given the restrictive RVOL threshold (A-03), this scenario will occur on 40-60% of trading days.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Without a protocol, the system will either (a) do nothing and miss the daily compounding target, or (b) lower its
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: filters in desperation and take a low-quality trade that is more likely to lose.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : On no-signal days, the operator faces an unstructured decision: accept a zero-return day (which breaks the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compounding curve) or manually override the system to force a trade (which introduces discretionary risk). Neither
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: option is acceptable for a systematic trading operation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Implement an escalation cascade that progressively relaxes filters as the day progresses without a signal:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 14:00 UK: Lower RVOL threshold by 0.3 (e.g., 2.0 becomes 1.7). Widen the ticker scan to include
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the 3 highest-RVOL tickers regardless of absolute threshold.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 14:30 UK: Lower confidence floor from 55 to 50. Enable the VWAP mean-reversion strategy even
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outside the lunch window.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 15:00 UK: Accept the best available signal with confidence >= 45, but at half-size.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 15:30 UK: FLAT. Officially declare a no-signal day. Do not force a trade. Log the day as 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NO
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SIGNAL
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in the outcomes database with PnL = 0. Update the Monte Carlo model with the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: zero-return day.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This cascade preserves signal quality while providing a structured response to quiet days.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A-07 | MEDIUM | CVaR is Per-Position, Not Portfolio-Wide
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Location
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: qualification/dynamic_sizer.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L130-134, L324-329
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Issue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The CVaR (Conditional Value-at-Risk) scaling in the dynamic sizer operates on a per-position basis. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computes the rolling 60-trade 5th-percentile expected shortfall and scales individual position sizes accordingly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Rockafellar 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:41,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Uryasev 2000). However, there is no portfolio-wide CVaR or CDaR (Conditional
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Drawdown-at-Risk) circuit breaker. A portfolio of 3 positions, each individually within CVaR limits, can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: collectively produce a drawdown that exceeds any acceptable portfolio-level threshold. This is especially acute
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: given the correlation issue described in F-03: three NASDAQ-correlated 3x ETPs that are individually within CVaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: limits can collectively produce a portfolio CVaR that is 2-3x the per-position estimate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The system manages tail risk per position but is blind to portfolio-level tail risk. A correlated drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: across all positions simultaneously -- precisely the scenario that leveraged NASDAQ ETPs are exposed to --
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bypasses all existing CVaR protections.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Implement a two-tier CVaR framework: (1) retain per-trade CVaR scaling in the dynamic sizer as-is, and (2)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: add a portfolio-wide CDaR circuit breaker. The CDaR breaker should compute the maximum expected drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: duration at the 5th percentile across all open positions, accounting for pairwise correlations from the Ledoit-Wolf
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: covariance matrix. If portfolio CDaR exceeds 5% of equity, reduce all position sizes to half. If portfolio CDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exceeds 8%, flatten to a single position (the one with the lowest correlation to the rest). This creates a nested
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: defence: CVaR protects individual positions, CDaR protects the portfolio.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AUDIT CERTIFICATION
