   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Liu (2015)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: multiple-testing correction — when scanning 12 instruments simultaneously, the single-asset significance threshold must
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be raised to control family-wise error rate. At 75/100, the false discovery rate is held below 5%.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.1.3 Adaptive Easing for Leveraged ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In strong trending regimes (as classified by the HMM regime detector in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cross_asset_macro.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ), the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consensus thresholds ease to capture momentum continuation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Regime | Standard Threshold | Eased Threshold | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG | 7.0 / 10.0 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.8 / 9.5 | Jegadeesh 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Titman (1993): momentum profits concentrate in strong trends. Tighter threshold = missed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: alpha |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | All Other Regimes | 7.0 / 10.0 | No easing | Default conservatism preserves capital |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.1.4 P90 Spread Tracker (Dynamic Cost Awareness)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system maintains a rolling 20-day P90 spread for each ETP, updated every trading session. This is critical for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leveraged ETPs where bid-ask spreads can blow out 3-5x during volatile periods.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spread Score
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 100 - (current
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spread / p90
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spread) x 100
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If current spread > 2.5x the 3-day median spread, the instrument is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VETOED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  regardless of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: P90 (not mean) is used because spread distributions are heavily right-skewed — the mean understates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: typical costs while the P90 captures the realistic 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: worst normal day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  scenario
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.1.5 Power Hour Seasonality Boost
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Per Heston, Korajczyk 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sadka (2010), intraday returns exhibit statistically significant periodicity, with the last
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trading hour showing elevated momentum continuation. S15 applies a +15% confidence boost to signals generated
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: during Power Hour (14:30-15:15 UK for LSE-listed ETPs that track US underlyings opening at 14:30 UK).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This boost is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: multiplicative
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , not additive: a raw confidence of 70 becomes 70 x 1.15 = 80.5, which clears the 75
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: floor. This is intentional — it captures the empirical reality that US-open momentum spills into LSE ETPs during this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: window.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.2 Fund-First Mandatory Execution Logic (NEW — v13.0 Enhancement)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.2.1 The ISA Tax-Shield Imperative
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The UK ISA wrapper eliminates capital gains tax entirely. For a system targeting 14,757% annualised returns, this is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not a minor convenience — it is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: structural alpha
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  worth hundreds of thousands of pounds per year at scale. Every
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trade that can be routed through an ISA-eligible LSE ETP 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: must
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  be routed there.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.2.2 Execution Priority Cascade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: During LSE hours (08:00 — 16:30 UK), the following priority cascade governs every execution decision:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SIGNAL DETECTED ON UNDERLYING (e.g., NVIDIA momentum breakout)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ├─ Step 1: Query lse_mapper.get_etp_equivalent("NVDA")
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │           Returns: {"3x_long": "NVD3.L", "3x_inverse":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "NVDS.L"}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ├─ Step 2: Is LSE currently open?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │   ├─ YES → Route to NVD3.L (3x amplification, tax-free)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │   └─ NO  → Log opportunity as MISSED. Do NOT execute on US
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exchange.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │            (Current system has no after-hours capability — see
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §2.2.4)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ├─ Step 3: Is ETP spread acceptable? (< 2.5x median_3d_spread)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │   ├─ YES → Execute via ETP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │   └─ NO  → Wait 60 seconds, re-quote. If still wide → VETO
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     │
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     └─ Step 4: ETP overnight_kill check
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         ├─ 5x ETP → Set hard exit at 15:30 UK (no exceptions)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         └─ 3x ETP → Position eligible for overnight hold
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.2.3 Atomic Mutual Exclusion Rule
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NEVER enter long QQQ3.L AND short QQQS.L in the same trading session.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Although the codebase permits simultaneous long + inverse positions (no explicit veto exists in the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: INVERSE_PAIRS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  logic), doing so is economically incoherent and creates a synthetic straddle with guaranteed vol
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drag on both legs. The rebalancing mechanics of leveraged ETPs mean that holding both sides simultaneously
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: guarantees negative expected value over any holding period exceeding a few hours (Cheng 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Madhavan 2009).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Before entering any position, check the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: INVERSE_PAIRS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  mapping:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: INVERSE_PAIRS = {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "QQQ3.L": "QQQS.L",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "3LUS.L": "3USS.L",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "NVD3.L": "NVDS.L",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "TSL3.L": "TSLS.L"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If the inverse counterpart is currently held, the new signal is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VETOED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . The existing position
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s direction was chosen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by the earlier, higher-confidence signal — honour that decision.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exception
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : If Smart Money Alignment (derived from VPIN in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: virtual_trader.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and volume profile POC
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: analysis) flips decisively mid-session (VPIN > 0.85 indicating toxic flow reversal), the system may close the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: existing position AND enter the inverse. This is a reversal, not a hedge. The old position exits fully before the new
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one enters. Sequence: CLOSE → WAIT 30s → RE-SCORE → ENTER INVERSE (if confidence > 80).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.2.4 Night Shift — Architectural Gap Declaration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HONEST ASSESSMENT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The current NZT-48 codebase has 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: zero
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  after-hours US trading capability. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: daily_target.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  returns an empty signal set outside the 09:00-15:15 UK window. There is no 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Night Shift
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: module. There is no extended-hours data feed. There is no broker integration for US after-hours execution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This means approximately 65% of the 24-hour cycle is unmonitored and untradeable. Given Lou, Polk 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Skouras
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (2019) finding that the equity premium is earned 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entirely overnight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (the intraday return on the S
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: P 500 is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: approximately zero over multi-decade samples), this represents a significant missed opportunity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 3 Enhancement Plan
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (post paper-trading validation):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Add US extended-hours data feed (Polygon.io or similar)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Build 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: strategies/night_shift.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — overnight momentum capture on US-listed ETFs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Integrate with ISA-eligible US stocks (not ETPs — these don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t trade after LSE close)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Target: capture overnight gap for next-day LSE ETP positioning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For v13.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Night Shift is documented as future work. All compounding projections assume LSE-hours-only
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: execution (approximately 7.25 hours per trading day). The 2% daily target must be achievable within this window.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.3 Directional Parity — The Dual-Blade (NEW — v13.0 Core Enhancement)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.3.1 Regime-Dependent Directional Filtering
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The NZT-48 system
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s ability to profit in both rising AND falling markets is its most important structural advantage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: over long-only strategies. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: INVERSE_PAIRS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  mapping in the codebase already supports this — what v13.0 adds is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime-aware directional filtering
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to prevent the system from fighting the macro tide.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Regime (from HMM) | Eligible Direction | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG | LONG only |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Moskowitz, Ooi 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Pedersen (2012): time-series momentum has Sharpe > 1.0 in strong trends. Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t fight it. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MOD | LONG preferred, INVERSE allowed if confidence > 85 | Moderate trends can reverse.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Allow high-conviction inverse entries. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | RANGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BOUND | Both eligible | No directional bias. Highest confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: score wins regardless of direction. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MOD | INVERSE preferred, LONG allowed if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence > 85 | Mirror of TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MOD. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG | INVERSE only | Daniel 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Moskowitz (2016): momentum crashes are brutal (-91.6% in 2 months). Only inverse positions survive. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF | INVERSE only | VIX > 30, credit spreads widening, HMM in stressed state. Capital preservation mode. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SHOCK | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NO TRADING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | System goes flat. No new entries. Existing positions managed via Chandelier Exit only. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.3.2 The Inverse Pivot — Crash Monetisation Protocol
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When markets transition from TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP to TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOWN, the system must execute an 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Inverse Pivot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: closing long positions and rotating into inverse ETPs. This is the single most valuable trade the system can make,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because leveraged inverse ETPs in a genuine crash can return 20-50% in a single session.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: However, the entry must be precise. Daniel 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Moskowitz (2016) document that momentum crashes are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: characterised by an initial violent spike followed by mean-reversion whipsaws that destroy poorly-timed entries. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: protocol:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Inverse Pivot Entry Criteria (ALL must be true):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VIX > 28.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Confirmed fear regime. VIX 20-28 is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: elevated concern
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; above 28.5 is genuine risk-off
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Whaley 2000). The 28.5 threshold is the 90th percentile of VIX readings since 2010.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Underlying Price 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  50-period EMA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — The trend has broken. Price below the 50 EMA confirms the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: move is structural, not a noise spike. Using 50 periods (not 20) avoids false triggers from normal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pullbacks within uptrends.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Move Within 24 Hours of Initial Spike
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Momentum crashes cluster in time (Daniel 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Moskowitz
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2016). The first 24 hours capture 60-70% of the total move. After 24 hours, mean-reversion forces
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: strengthen and the inverse trade becomes a coin flip.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Enter on FIRST RETRACEMENT, Not the Spike Itself
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — During the initial spike, spreads on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: inverse ETPs blow out to 5-10x normal. The P90 spread tracker will veto any entry during this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: window. Wait for the first pullback (typically 30-60 minutes after the initial move), confirm spreads
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have normalised (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2.5x median
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spread), then enter.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position Size: 0.3 x f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (30% Kelly)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Kelly criterion (Kelly 1956) gives the growth-optimal fraction, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: full Kelly on inverse ETPs during crashes is reckless. The payoff distribution is extremely fat-tailed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in both directions. 30% Kelly limits the damage if the crash reverses (bear trap), while still capturing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: meaningful profit if it continues. Barroso 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Santa-Clara (2015) show that vol-scaling momentum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: positions (which is what 30% Kelly approximates) doubles the Sharpe ratio from 0.53 to 0.97 while
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: halving maximum drawdown.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Maximum Hold: 24 Hours
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Inverse leveraged ETPs suffer from compounding decay (also called 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: volatility drag
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beta slippage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) that erodes returns over multi-day holds (Cheng 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Madhavan
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2009). In a -5% crash day, QQQS.L (3x inverse) returns approximately +15% (minus friction). But
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: holding for 3 days in a choppy decline, the cumulative return may be only +8% instead of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expected +15%. The 24-hour maximum enforces discipline.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dynamic Momentum Scaling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Per Barroso 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Santa-Clara (2015), position size is inversely proportional to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trailing 60-day realised volatility of the underlying. When vol is high (crash conditions), the position is already
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: smaller — this is the built-in crash protection.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position_size = target_vol / (realised_vol_60d * leverage_factor) *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: capital
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For a 3x inverse ETP on NASDAQ-100 with realised vol at 35% (crash level):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position_size = 0.15 / (0.35 * 3) * 10000 = 0.15 / 1.05 * 10000 =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GBP 1,428.57
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is 14.3% of capital — aggressive enough to matter, conservative enough to survive a bear-trap reversal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.3.3 Flash Crash Hedge (Existing Capability — Documented)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The codebase already contains an automatic flash crash hedge that triggers inverse ETP purchase when the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: underlying drops > 0.5% in a short window. This is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: portfolio protection
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  mechanism, not a profit-seeking trade:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger: underlying drops > 0.5% from session high
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action: purchase inverse ETP counterpart (from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: INVERSE_PAIRS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  mapping)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Size: minimal (capital preservation, not profit maximisation)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Duration: until underlying stabilises or session ends
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This complements the Inverse Pivot (which is a deliberate, scored trade) by providing automatic downside hedging
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for existing long positions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.4 Intraday Momentum Exploitation (NEW — Based on Gao, Han, Li 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhou
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2018, JFE)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.4.1 The First-Half-Hour / Last-Half-Hour Predictability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gao et al. (2018) document a striking empirical regularity: the return in the first 30 minutes of the trading session is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a statistically significant predictor of the return in the last 30 minutes. This effect is robust across US equity markets,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: persists out-of-sample, and generates economically meaningful alpha after transaction costs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The mechanism is believed to be 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: informed trading clustering
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : institutional traders who receive information
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: overnight execute in the first 30 minutes (when liquidity is deepest), and the price discovery process continues into
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the close as the information diffuses to slower participants.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.4.2 Application to LSE ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For LSE-listed ETPs tracking US underlyings, the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: first 30 minutes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  window is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 08:00-08:30 UK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (LSE open), and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: last 30 minutes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 15:30-16:00 UK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (approaching LSE close, overlapping with US mid-morning).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation Rules:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | First-30-Min Return (08:00-08:30 UK) | Action | Confidence Modifier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | > +0.5% | LONG bias for the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: session | +5 to S15 confidence score for long ETPs |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -0.5% | SHORT bias for the session | +5 to S15 confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: score for inverse ETPs |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Between -0.5% and +0.5% | No bias | No modifier (insufficient signal strength) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Critical Design Decision
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : This is an 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: additive modifier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to the existing S15 scoring system, NOT a standalone signal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: generator. A +5 confidence boost can turn a marginal signal (score 72) into a firing signal (score 77), but it cannot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: create a signal from nothing. This prevents the intraday momentum signal from overriding the comprehensive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 8-indicator consensus.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.4.3 Interaction with US Open (14:30 UK)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 14:30 UK US market open creates a second intraday momentum inflection. The first-30-min signal from 08:00
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UK may be reinforced or contradicted by the US open direction. Rules:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If 08:00-08:30 signal and 14:30-15:00 US-open direction 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agree
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : confidence boost doubles to +10
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If they 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: disagree
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : confidence boost reverts to 0 (conflicting signals cancel)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If US open moves > 1.0% in either direction: this overrides the morning signal entirely (US
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: institutions are the marginal price setter for these ETPs)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.5 Five Enhancements (E-01 through E-05)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E-01: Chain Reaction Confidence Boost
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Current State
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: move_attribution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  module identifies when a move in one ticker propagates to correlated
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tickers (e.g., NVIDIA earnings beat → NVD3.L spike → QQQ3.L sympathy move → 3SEM.L follows). Currently, this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: attribution data is logged but not wired into S15 scoring.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Enhancement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Feed 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: move_attribution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  output directly into the S15 confidence calculation as a supplementary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: indicator.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Calibration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The existing codebase uses a fixed beta of 0.40 (Thomas 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang 2006 estimate for sector momentum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spillover). This is a population average that ignores pair-specific dynamics. Replace with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: empirical pair-specific
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beta
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  estimated from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outcomes.jsonl
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each pair (source_ticker, target_ticker):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     beta_empirical = cov(source_return, target_return) /
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: var(source_return)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     # Estimated from last 60 completed trades in outcomes.jsonl
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     # Shrunk toward 0.40 prior with weight = min(n_observations /
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 30, 1.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Chain Boost Calculation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chain_boost = min(beta_empirical * source_move_zscore * 10, 20)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Capped at +20 confidence points to prevent a single chain event
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from dominating
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cap Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : A +20 cap means a chain reaction can boost a score from 55 to 75 (minimum firing threshold), but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cannot single-handedly push a weak signal past the threshold. The chain reaction must combine with at least
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: moderate standalone merit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E-02: PEAD Power-Law Decay (Chan, Jegadeesh 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Lakonishok 1996)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Background
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Post-Earnings Announcement Drift (PEAD) is one of the most robust anomalies in empirical finance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After an earnings surprise, stocks continue to drift in the direction of the surprise for 60-90 trading days (Ball 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Brown 1968, Bernard 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Thomas 1989, Chan, Jegadeesh 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Lakonishok 1996).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Current Gap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : NZT-48 has no earnings-aware signal component. When a leveraged ETP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s underlying reports
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: earnings, the system treats the next day identically to any other day — missing the most predictable drift in equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: markets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Enhancement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Add a PEAD residual component to S15 scoring:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pead_residual(t) = 0.30 * (t + 1)^(-0.5)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = trading days since earnings announcement (t=0 on announcement day)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.30 = initial PEAD impulse (calibrated to the average standardised unexpected earnings coefficient
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from Chan et al. 1996)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (t + 1)^(-0.5)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: power-law decay
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , NOT exponential decay
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why Power-Law, Not Exponential
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Exponential decay (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.30 * e^(-0.1t)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) drops to near-zero by day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 20. But the empirical PEAD literature consistently shows drift persisting for 60-90 days, with slow decay.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Power-law functions 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t^(-alpha)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: alpha
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.3, 0.7
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  match the observed decay profile far better (Hou, Xue 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang 2020). At 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: alpha = 0.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Days Post-Earnings | Power-Law Residual | Exponential Residual |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Day 1 | 0.212 | 0.271 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Day 5 | 0.122
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 0.182 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Day 10 | 0.090 | 0.110 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Day 20 | 0.065 | 0.041 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Day 40 | 0.047 | 0.005 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Day 60 | 0.039 | 0.001 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The power-law residual remains meaningful at day 40-60, capturing the well-documented slow tail of PEAD. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exponential residual is essentially zero by day 30, leaving alpha on the table.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Data Source
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Earnings dates from yfinance 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .info["earningsDate"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or fallback to Earnings Whispers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scrape. Store in Redis with TTL of 90 days.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E-03: Vol-Managed Sizing (Moreira 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Muir 2017, JF)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Background
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Moreira 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Muir (2017) demonstrate that scaling portfolio exposure inversely by recent realised
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: volatility improves Sharpe ratios across virtually all asset classes, without requiring return forecasts. The intuition:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: high volatility predicts high future volatility (vol clustering), but does NOT predict higher returns — so reducing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exposure during high-vol periods improves risk-adjusted returns mechanically.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Application to Leveraged ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : For 3x ETPs, the effective volatility is 3x the underlying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s realised vol. For 5x
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETPs, it is 5x. The vol-managed sizing formula:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weight_etp = (target_vol / (realised_vol_underlying *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leverage_factor)) * base_weight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: target_vol
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 15% annualised (system-level risk budget)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: realised_vol_underlying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 20-day Yang-Zhang estimator on the underlying index/stock
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Yang 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang 2000 — superior to close-to-close for instruments with gaps)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leverage_factor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 3 for 3x ETPs, 5 for 5x ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: base_weight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = Kelly-optimal weight from existing position sizer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Example
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : NVIDIA 20-day realised vol = 45%. NVD3.L is 3x leveraged.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weight = 0.15 / (0.45 * 3) * base_weight = 0.15 / 1.35 *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: base_weight = 0.111 * base_weight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This scales the position to 11.1% of what the base weight would suggest — aggressive vol compression that prevents a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: single high-vol trade from dominating portfolio P
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5x ETP Override
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : For 5x instruments, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is additionally capped at 10% of total capital regardless of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: formula output. The fat tails on 5x daily rebalanced products are extreme enough that even vol-managed sizing can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: understate risk during regime transitions (Avellaneda 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang 2010).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E-04: Inverse Pivot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fully described in Section 2.3.2 above. Reference implementation targets 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: strategies/daily_target.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with new method 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _evaluate_inverse_pivot()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  called when regime transitions to TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOWN or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E-05: No-Signal Escalation Protocol
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : On some trading days, no instrument in the 12-ticker core universe meets the 75/100 confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold. The system produces zero signals. While 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no trade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is a valid outcome (and far better than forcing a bad
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trade), an excessive dry-day frequency indicates the confidence floor is too restrictive for current market conditions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Escalation Timeline (all times UK):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Time | Action | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 09:00 - 14:00 | Normal S15 scanning with confidence floor = 75 | Standard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operation. Most signals fire between 09:30 and 11:00 (LSE morning session) or 14:45-15:15 (US open spillover). |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 14:00 | Lower confidence floor: 75 → 70 | 5 hours of scanning with no signal suggests the day is marginal. A 70 floor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: still represents strong conviction (above the 95th percentile of random signals per Harvey 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Liu 2015), but captures
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: near-miss opportunities. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 14:30 | Activate S12 Rebalance Flow scan | S12 targets predictable end-of-day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rebalancing flows in leveraged ETPs (Mathis 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Moerke 2022). These flows are most exploitable when the main
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: session has been range-bound (which is exactly when S15 finds no signal). |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 15:00 | Activate S16 Universal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scanner | S16 broadens the search beyond the 12-ticker core to the full 35-ticker universe. This catches opportunities
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in secondary ETPs that S15
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s core filter excluded. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 15:30 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Accept FLAT day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | If no signal has fired by 15:30, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system accepts a zero-trade day. Forcing a trade into the last 30 minutes of the session — when spreads widen and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rebalancing flows distort prices — is negative expected value. Discipline over desperation. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:42,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Adaptive Gate Widening
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The system tracks dry-day frequency as a rolling 20-day metric. If dry days exceed 8%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of trading days (approximately 1.6 days per 20-day window), the ADR gate is widened from 2.9% to 2.5%. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: admits instruments with slightly lower daily range potential, increasing the opportunity set without materially
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compromising the 2% target (2.5% ADR still provides sufficient range for 2% capture after spread costs on a 3x
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETP).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dry-Day Logging
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Every flat day is logged with full context — all 12 tickers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  scores, the highest-scoring instrument,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the reason it failed (which indicator vetoed), and the macro regime. This data feeds the quarterly model recalibration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Harvey 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Liu 2020 — replication crisis in factor investing demands ongoing validation).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.6 ETP Rebalancing Alpha (NEW — Based on Mathis 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Moerke 2022)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.6.1 The Mechanical Rebalancing Flow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Leveraged ETPs must rebalance their exposure at the end of each trading day to maintain their target leverage ratio.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This creates 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: predictable, non-informational order flow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in the last 30 minutes of trading:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Market Day | ETP Action at Close | Direction of Rebalancing Flow |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Strong UP day (+2%+) | Long ETP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: must BUY more underlying to restore 3x ratio | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BUY flow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — pushes underlying (and ETP) higher |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Strong DOWN day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (-2%+) | Long ETP must SELL underlying to de-lever | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SELL flow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — pushes underlying (and ETP) lower |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Flat day (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0.5% move) | Minimal rebalancing needed | Negligible flow |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mathis 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Moerke (2022) quantify this effect and show it is economically significant for highly-levered products.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The larger the daily move, the larger the rebalancing flow, and the more predictable the last-30-minute price action.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.6.2 Exploitation Rules for NZT-48
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 1: DO NOT enter new positions in the last 30 minutes (15:00-15:30 UK for LSE ETPs).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The rebalancing flow creates a temporarily distorted price that reverts overnight. Entering at 15:15 on a strong
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: up-day means buying into mechanical buy flow that will not persist — the ETP price is momentarily inflated by its own
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rebalancing. The next morning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s open will correct this, starting your position at a loss.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 2: If holding a position, the rebalancing flow HELPS your trailing stop.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you are long QQQ3.L on a day the NASDAQ-100 is up 2%+, the end-of-day rebalancing buy flow pushes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: QQQ3.L higher, extending your profit and pulling your Chandelier Exit trailing stop upward. This is free alpha — the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rebalancing flow acts as a tailwind for existing positions that are already in profit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 3: Bank 33% at Rung 2 BEFORE the rebalancing window.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 5-rung profit ladder in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/chandelier_exit.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Le Beau 1999 adaptation) banks partial profits at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: predefined levels. Rung 2 (33% of position) should be exited by 14:55 UK — before the rebalancing window begins.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This locks in gains at a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clean
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  price, uncontaminated by mechanical flow. The remaining 67% rides the rebalancing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tailwind with a tighter trailing stop.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 4: For 5x ETPs with overnight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: kill=True, EXIT BEFORE REBALANCING.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5x ETPs have larger rebalancing flows and more extreme vol drag. The rebalancing window for these instruments is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: particularly dangerous because:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The flow is larger (5x leverage = 5x rebalancing volume)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spread widens during rebalancing as market makers absorb the flow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 5x product MUST be closed before session end regardless
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exit 5x positions by 15:00 UK at the latest. Do not attempt to ride the rebalancing flow.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.6.3 Rebalancing Flow Estimation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: To estimate the magnitude of the expected rebalancing flow (useful for adjusting trailing stop tightness):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rebalancing_flow_pct = (leverage_factor - 1) * daily_return *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (AUM_etp / ADV_underlying)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leverage_factor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 3 or 5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: daily_return
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = underlying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s return so far today
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AUM_etp
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = ETP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s assets under management (from provider data, refreshed weekly)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ADV_underlying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = average daily volume of underlying index/stock
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rebalancing_flow_pct
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  > 0.5% of ADV, the flow is material and the rules above are strictly enforced.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Below 0.5%, the flow is noise and can be ignored.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SECTION 3: THE APEX RADAR — Global Cross-Asset Intelligence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Drone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Status
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : This module does NOT exist in the current codebase. It must be built from scratch.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Target File
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: strategies/apex_scout.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Purpose
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Asynchronous discovery of anomalous relative volume (RVOL) events across a broad universe of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 200-500 pre-filtered global equities, feeding high-conviction signals to the Vanguard Sniper (Section 2) via the ISA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Priority Mapping layer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,146:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.1 Purpose and Strategic Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.1.1 The Discovery Gap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Vanguard Sniper (S15) is a precision instrument: it scores 12 known ETPs against 8 indicators and fires exactly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1 signal per day. Its weakness is that it only sees what it already knows. If a stock outside the 12-ticker core universe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: experiences a massive institutional accumulation event — the kind of move that would produce a 20%+ day on a 3x
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETP — S15 is blind to it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Apex Radar exists to solve this. It continuously scans a broad universe (200-500 tickers), identifies anomalous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: volume events in real-time, maps them to ISA-eligible LSE ETPs where possible, and feeds the highest-conviction
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discovery to S15 for execution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.1.2 Volume as the Leading Indicator
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Volume precedes price. This is not speculation; it is one of the most replicated findings in market microstructure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Karpoff 1987, Llorente et al. 2002, Chordia 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Swaminathan 2000). When institutional investors accumulate a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position, they cannot do so invisibly — the volume footprint appears before the price impact is fully realised. RVOL
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (relative volume vs. time-of-day-adjusted 20-day average) is the cleanest measure of this anomalous activity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.2 Architecture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.2.1 Class Design
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # strategies/apex_scout.py
