   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  30 seconds. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.6.3 Sunday Universe Construction (Pre-Filter Pipeline)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Sunday pipeline processes the full Russell 3000 (plus selected international ADRs) down to a focused watchlist
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of 200-500 tickers. This is the most computationally expensive operation and runs once per week:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STAGE 1: Download Russell 3000 daily OHLCV (last 60 trading days)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          Source: yfinance batch download
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          Time: ~10 minutes for 3,000 tickers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STAGE 2: Compute screening metrics for each ticker:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - RVOL_20d: mean relative volume over 20 days
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - ADR_20d: average daily range over 20 days (must be >
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.0%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - Market Cap: exclude < $500M (insufficient liquidity for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETP tracking)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - Sector: GICS classification for factor group mapping
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STAGE 3: Composite ranking:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          score = 0.50 * rank(RVOL_20d) + 0.30 * rank(ADR_20d) +
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.20 * rank(MarketCap)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          Rationale: RVOL is the primary signal (50% weight),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          ADR ensures the ticker can deliver 2% moves (30% weight),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          MarketCap ensures liquidity and ETP availability (20%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weight)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STAGE 4: Filter to top 200-500 by composite score
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - Hard floor: ADR_20d > 2.0% (below this, 2% daily target
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is not mechanically achievable)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - Hard floor: average daily volume > $5M (below this,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: slippage destroys edge)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - Soft cap: 500 tickers max (yfinance rate limit budget)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          - If < 200 qualify: widen ADR floor to 1.5% (rare, only in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extreme low-vol regimes)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STAGE 5: Store in Redis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          Key: apex:watchlist
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          Value: JSON array of {ticker, rvol_20d, adr_20d, sector,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: market_cap, lse_etp_equivalent}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          TTL: 7 days (auto-expires before next Sunday refresh)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.6.4 Graceful Degradation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If yfinance rate limits are hit during market hours:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: First limit hit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Back off 30 seconds, retry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Second consecutive limit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Reduce batch size from 50 to 25 tickers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Third consecutive limit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Reduce watchlist to top 100 by RVOL rank (highest-probability anomalies
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Persistent rate limiting (> 5 minutes)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Fall back to 60-minute scan interval (half frequency)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Total yfinance failure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Log ALERT, continue with S15 core universe only (12 tickers from cached
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: At no point does a data feed failure cause the system to halt. The Vanguard Sniper (S15) operates independently on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: its core 12-ticker universe and does not depend on the Apex Radar. The Scout is additive alpha, not a dependency.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.7 Signal Output Format
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When the Apex Radar identifies a qualifying anomaly, it produces an 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AnomalySignal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  object that enters the S15
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: evaluation queue:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: @dataclass
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: class AnomalySignal:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ticker: str                  # Original ticker (e.g., "NVDA")
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     lse_etp: Optional[str]      # Rerouted ETP (e.g., "NVD3.L") or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: None
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     rvol: float                  # Current relative volume
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     z_score: float               # Z-score vs. 20-observation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: history
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     regime: str                  # Market regime at time of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: detection
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     vwap_aligned: bool           # Price > VWAP confirmed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     stranger_discount: float     # Bayesian penalty (0.70-1.00)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     trigger_source: str          # "scheduled" | "nasdaq_burst" |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "vix_spike" | etc.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     isa_eligible: bool           # HMRC ISA qualification confirmed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     spread_ok: bool              # < 2.5x median_3d_spread
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     gap_stabilised: bool         # G-R2 wait completed (if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: applicable)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     timestamp: datetime          # UTC timestamp of detection
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     @property
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def adjusted_confidence(self) -> float:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Confidence score after Stranger Penalty,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         ready for S15 integration.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         base = min(self.z_score * 20, 100)  # Scale Z-score to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0-100
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return base * self.stranger_discount
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: S15 treats Scout signals identically to its own candidates: they must clear the 75/100 confidence floor (after Stranger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Penalty), pass the tail risk pre-screen, and compete against core universe signals on equal terms. The only special
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: treatment is the Stranger Penalty itself, which decays to zero as the ticker becomes familiar.
