   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SECTION 4: THE EXECUTIONER -- Stoikov EV Gate + Infinite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Profit Ladder
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This section specifies the complete execution pipeline from signal acceptance through position lifecycle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: management. Every component has been stress-tested against the 40 bps round-trip spread drag that Gemini R2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: correctly identified as the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compounding killer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  on 3x leveraged ETPs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.1 Current Execution Flow (Verified from Codebase)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The execution pipeline is a strict sequential chain. No stage may be bypassed, no shortcut exists. A signal must
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: survive every gate or it is discarded.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stage 1: Signal Generation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     S15 DailyTarget fires once per day at pre-market scan (07:45
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UTC).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Scores all 18 ISA-eligible tickers by "2% reachability"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: composite.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Best candidate wins. Ties broken by lower spread_bps.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stage 2: 33-Gate Gauntlet
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Signal passes through the full gauntlet:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Regime gate (HMM state != RISK_OFF, != SHOCK)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - ML meta-label gate (ensemble P(profit) >= threshold)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Stoikov EV gate (net expected return > 1.5 * stop_distance)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Spread gate (bid-ask spread < ETP threshold)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Liquidity gate (ADV_20d sufficient for position size)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Volatility regime gate (not in vol compression below ATR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: floor)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Correlation gate (incremental portfolio correlation check)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - CVaR gate (position-level tail risk)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - CDaR gate (portfolio-level serial drawdown)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - CUSUM alpha reaper gate (strategy not in decay)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Heat cap gate (max exposure per ticker)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - ... remaining gates per gauntlet specification (Section 3)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ANY single gate veto = signal rejected. No override. No manual
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bypass.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stage 3: Position Sizing (DynamicSizer)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     8-factor Kelly computation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       f* = edge / odds, scaled by regime multiplier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Capped by: portfolio heat, per-ticker heat, max drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: budget
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Inputs: win_rate, avg_win, avg_loss, regime, volatility,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:               correlation_load, CDaR_headroom, account_equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stage 4: Execution Planning (ExecutionPlanner)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Cost-aware execution plan:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Compute spread cost (bid-ask at time of entry)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Compute net R:R after spread deduction
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - If net R:R < 1.5:1 after costs --> VETO (cost-aware
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rejection)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Select order type: LIMIT preferred, MARKET only if urgency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: > threshold
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Set time-in-force: GTC for limit, IOC for market
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stage 5: Position Opening (VirtualTrader)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Paper-mode execution:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Log entry price, timestamp, position size, stop level,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: target level
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Record all gate scores for post-hoc analysis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Persist to SQLite (trades table) + Redis (active_positions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hash)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - Confirm Redis WAIT for synchronous persistence (v13.0 fix)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stage 6: Position Management (ChandelierExit)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     5-rung profit ladder manages the position lifecycle.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     See Section 4.4 for complete ladder specification.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     All rung transitions persisted to Redis with WAIT confirmation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Invariant
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : No human intervention at any stage. The system is fully autonomous in paper mode. Every decision is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: logged with full provenance for post-hoc audit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2 Bayesian Stranger Penalty (Replacing Static 0.5x Multiplier)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem Statement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The current system applies a static 0.5x position-size multiplier to any ticker that has fewer than some arbitrary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold of historical trades. This is crude. A ticker with 49 trades at a 3.2 DSR (daily Sharpe ratio) should not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: receive the same penalty as a ticker with 2 trades at a 0.8 DSR. The penalty must be a continuous function of both
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sample size and demonstrated edge quality.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Formula
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Bayesian stranger penalty kappa is computed as:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: kappa(n, DSR) = kappa_min + (kappa_max - kappa_min) * f_DSR(DSR) *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_n(n)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where the two component functions are:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_DSR(DSR) = 1 - exp(-lambda * max(0, DSR - DSR_min))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_n(n)     = n / (n + n_0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Parameter Values
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Parameter | v12.0 | Gemini R2 Proposal | v13.0 (FINAL) | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-----------|-------|-------------------|---------------|-----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | kappa
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: min | 0.50 (static) | 0.25 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.25
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Floor penalty: even
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a completely unknown ticker gets 25% of full Kelly, not 50%. This is more conservative for a GBP 10K account
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where a single large loss on an unknown name is existential. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | kappa
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max | 0.50 (static) | 1.00 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.00
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Ceiling: a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: well-known ticker with strong DSR and deep sample earns full Kelly. No artificial cap. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | lambda | N/A | 0.8 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT modified
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Gemini R2 originally proposed 0.8 but then correctly noted this is too aggressive for a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GBP 10K base. At lambda=0.8, a ticker with DSR=2.5 already gets f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR=0.55, which is too generous given the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: small account. At lambda=0.5, the same ticker gets f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR=0.39, forcing more trades before full sizing. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | n
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0 | N/A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 30 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT modified
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Gemini R2 originally proposed 30 but then correctly noted that 30 trades can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cluster in a single volatility regime (e.g., 30 trades all in TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG). At n
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0=50, the half-life is 50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trades, requiring broader regime coverage before convergence. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | DSR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: min | N/A | 1.5 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Minimum DSR before
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: any credit is given. Below 1.5, the ticker has not demonstrated sufficient edge to deserve anything above kappa
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: min.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
