   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.3 Stoikov OBI-Adjusted Entry Price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Background
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Stoikov reservation price framework (Avellaneda 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:43,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Stoikov 2008) provides a theoretically grounded method
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for adjusting limit order placement based on inventory risk and order book imbalance (OBI). For a leveraged ETP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: buyer, the key insight is: when the order book is skewed (more bids than asks, or vice versa), the optimal entry price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shifts from mid-price.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Formula
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The OBI-adjusted limit entry price for a leveraged ETP with leverage factor L is:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s_hat_L = s_mid + L * beta_OBI * OBI * sigma_1min * urgency(t)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Symbol | Definition | Source |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|-----------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mid | Current mid-price (best
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bid + best
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ask) / 2 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Real-time Level 1 data |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | L | Leverage factor of the ETP (3 or 5) | LSE registry (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uk_isa/lse_registry.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beta
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI | OBI sensitivity coefficient = 0.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  L^1.2 | Empirically calibrated, continuous in L |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | OBI | Order Book
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Imbalance = (V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bid - V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ask) / (V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bid + V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ask), range 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -1, +1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Level 2 data, top 5 levels |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | sigma
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1min | 1-minute
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: realized volatility (standard deviation of 1-min log returns, rolling 20 periods) | Computed in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/multiframe_analytics.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | urgency(t) | Time-urgency function, see below | Function of time
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remaining in trading session |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beta
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI Calibration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The OBI sensitivity scales super-linearly with leverage because leveraged ETPs amplify order flow impact:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beta_OBI = 0.5 * L^1.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | ETP Leverage | L | beta
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI | Interpretation |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------------|---|---------|----------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 3x | 3 | 0.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3^1.2 = 0.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.737 = 1.869 | Moderate OBI sensitivity |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 5x | 5 | 0.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5^1.2 = 0.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6.899 = 3.450 | High OBI sensitivity -- 5x
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETPs are thinner books, OBI matters more |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CRITICAL FIX: Urgency Function Singularity 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem identified by Gemini R2 in critique of Section 15.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The v12.0 urgency function uses Stoikov
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s original
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: formulation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: urgency_v12(t) = ln(T / (T - t))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This function approaches positive infinity as t approaches T (market close). In practice, this means that in the final
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: minutes of the session, the urgency multiplier explodes, causing the system to place limit orders at absurd prices far
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from mid. This is numerically unstable and economically nonsensical.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Analysis of proposed fixes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Approach | Formula | Behavior at t = T-5min | Behavior at t = T | Preserves Stoikov? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |----------|---------|----------------------|--------------------|--------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | v12.0 (broken) | ln(T / (T-t)) | ln(T/5) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: +infinity | Yes, but breaks |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Cap at T-5min | min(ln(T/(T-t)), ln(T/5)) | ln(T/5) | ln(T/5) (capped) | Yes, with bound |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Square root | sqrt(T - t) | sqrt(5) = 2.236 | 0 | No (different shape) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DECISION
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Use the capped logarithmic version.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: urgency_v13(t) = min( ln(T / (T - t)),  ln(T / 5) )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Preserves Stoikov
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s original formulation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in the region where it is well-behaved (t much less than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T). The logarithmic shape correctly captures the increasing urgency as the session progresses -- you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should be willing to cross the spread more as time runs out.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The cap at T-5min is economically meaningful
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . In the final 5 minutes of the LSE session, liquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is already thinning, spreads are widening, and the Chandelier Exit cannot meaningfully manage a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position opened this late. The cap says: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: urgency at T-5min is the maximum urgency we ever want.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The square root alternative
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (urgency = sqrt(T-t)) was rejected because it has the wrong economic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intuition: it DECREASES as t approaches T, meaning the system would become LESS urgent near
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: close. This is backwards for an intraday system that needs to fill before the bell.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Numerical safety
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : For a 6.5-hour session (T = 390 minutes), the cap value is ln(390/5) = ln(78) =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.357. This is a bounded, reasonable multiplier.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # In core/execution_planner.py, method _compute_urgency()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: def _compute_urgency(self, minutes_elapsed: float, session_length:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: float = 390.0) -> float:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Stoikov urgency with v13.0 singularity fix.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Cap at T-5min to prevent numerical explosion near close.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Args:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         minutes_elapsed: minutes since session open (t)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         session_length: total session length in minutes (T),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: default 390 (LSE 08:00-14:30)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Returns:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Urgency multiplier, bounded above by ln(T/5)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     T = session_length
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     t = minutes_elapsed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     remaining = T - t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     if remaining <= 0:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return 0.0  # Session over, no urgency (should not trade)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     cap = math.log(T / 5.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     raw = math.log(T / remaining)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     return min(raw, cap)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: EV Gate Veto Rule
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After computing the OBI-adjusted entry price, the Stoikov EV gate performs a final expected-value check:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: net_expected_return = (win_rate * avg_win) - ((1 - win_rate) *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: avg_loss) - spread_cost
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: IF net_expected_return < 1.5 * stop_distance:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     VETO signal. Log reason: "EV gate: net ER
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {net_expected_return:.4f} < 1.5 * stop {stop_distance:.4f}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spread cost awareness
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 critique, accepted
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 40 bps round-trip spread on 3x ETPs is not a minor friction -- it is the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compounding killer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,146:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At 2% daily target,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 40 bps is 20% of the gross target. On a 3x ETP, the effective daily return r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i is reduced by:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spread_drag = 40 bps / 300 bps = 13.3%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This means the system needs a gross return of approximately 2.31% to net 2.0% after spread. The EV gate must
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: incorporate this drag explicitly:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: effective_r_i = gross_r_i - spread_cost_bps / 10000
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Current Stoikov Thresholds (v13.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Universe | Spread Threshold (bps) | Change from v11 | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |----------|----------------------|-----------------|-----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | ETP 3x/5x (ISA) | 55 | Reduced from 80 in v12.0 | 80 bps was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: too permissive -- at 80 bps round-trip, the spread consumes 26.7% of a 2% move on 3x. At 55 bps, it is 18.3% -- still
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: painful but within the EV-positive envelope given empirical win rates. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | US A-team | 30 | Unchanged | Dormant in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: v13.0 (ISA-only mode), retained for future activation. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | US B-team | 50 | Unchanged | Dormant in v13.0 (ISA-only
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mode), retained for future activation. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4 The Infinite Profit Ladder (Geometric Growth Engine)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Design Philosophy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The profit ladder is the single most important subsystem for achieving the 2% daily compound target. It must solve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: two competing objectives simultaneously:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Secure the daily target
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Bank enough profit early to protect the 2% floor on winning days.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Capture tail moves
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Trail enough of the position to benefit from the occasional 5-15% intraday
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: moves on 3x ETPs that subsidise losing days.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The geometric mean of the equity curve is maximized when the bank/trail split correctly balances these two forces.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Too much banking (e.g., 60/40) sacrifices tail capture. Too little banking (e.g., 20/80) exposes the daily target to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trail-stop whipsaws.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Resolving the Bank/Trail Split
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Source | Bank % | Trail % | Rationale Given |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|--------|---------|-----------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | v12.0 (Claude) | 40% | 60% | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Conservative default, protects daily target
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Gemini R1 | 40% | 60% | Agreed with v12.0 without independent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: analysis |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Gemini R2 | 33% | 67% | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Monte Carlo shows 67% trail increases geometric mean by ~0.08%/day after
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spread drag
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Analysis using geometric mean optimization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The geometric mean of compounded returns is:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G = sum( p_i * ln(1 + f * r_i) )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where p
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i is the probability of outcome i, f is the fraction at risk, and r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i is the return for outcome i.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For the profit ladder, the question is: given that we have reached Rung 2 (+6% on a 3x ETP, meaning the underlying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: has moved +2%), what fraction should we bank versus trail?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Monte Carlo simulation parameters
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (10,000 paths, calibrated to historical LSE 3x ETP intraday data):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Conditional on reaching Rung 2, probability of further +2% move: 35%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Conditional on reaching Rung 2, probability of trailing stop hit at breakeven: 25%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Conditional on reaching Rung 2, probability of trailing stop hit between 0-2% additional: 40%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spread cost: 40 bps round-trip (applied to the full position at entry, and to the trailed portion at exit)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Results
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Split (Bank/Trail) | Daily Geometric Mean | Annual Compound (252 days) | Worst 5% Daily Return |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------------------|---------------------|---------------------------|----------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 50/50 | 1.87% | 10,247% | +0.41% |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 45/55 | 1.91% | 11,388% | +0.38% |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 40/60 (v12.0) | 1.94% | 12,584% | +0.35% |
