   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DECISION
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Adopt 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 33% bank / 67% trail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 33/67 split sits at the geometric mean optimum. The key insight from Gemini R2 is correct: with 40 bps spread
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drag consuming 13.3% of the effective return, the tail capture from the 67% trail is MORE important than additional
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: banking security. The extra 7% in the trail (vs v12.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 60%) increases expected geometric mean by approximately
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.08%/day. Over 252 trading days, this compounds to roughly 22% more annual return.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 30/70 split was rejected because the worst-5% daily return drops to +0.22%, which is uncomfortably close to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: zero on bad trail days. The 33/67 maintains a +0.27% floor in the 5th percentile, providing adequate cushion.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Complete 5-Rung Ladder (v13.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RUNG 0: ENTRY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Trigger:     Position opened by VirtualTrader
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Stop:        -1R below entry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                For 3x ETPs: -1 * ATR_15min (typically 2.5-3.5% on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3x)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                Fallback:    -1.2% hard floor (if ATR < 1.2%, use
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.2%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Action:      Full position at risk. No profit yet.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Risk:        Maximum. This is the only rung where a loss is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Redis state: { rung: 0, stop: entry - 1R, banked: 0, trailing:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 100% }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RUNG 1: BREAKEVEN (Risk Elimination)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Trigger:     Price >= entry + 1.5 * ATR_15min
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Stop:        Move to BREAKEVEN (entry price + spread_cost)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                Note: breakeven includes spread recovery, not just
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entry price.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Action:      Risk eliminated. The trade is now "free."
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                No position adjustment. Full size still running.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Risk:        Zero (worst case: exit at breakeven minus slippage)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Redis state: { rung: 1, stop: entry + spread_bps, banked: 0,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trailing: 100% }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   CRITICAL: The stop at breakeven must include spread recovery.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Entry at 100.00 with 20 bps half-spread means true cost basis =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 100.20.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Breakeven stop = 100.20, not 100.00.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RUNG 2: DAILY TARGET SECURED (Bank 33%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Trigger:     Price >= entry * 1.06 (i.e., +6% on 3x ETP = +2%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: underlying)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Stop:        Ratchet to entry * 1.04 (lock +4% profit floor on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remaining 67%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Action:      BANK 33% of position at market.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                This is the daily compounding target. The 2% goal is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: secured.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                Log: "RUNG 2 BANK: {ticker} banked 33% at +6%,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: securing daily target"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Risk:        Minimal on banked portion. Trail risk on remaining
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 67%.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Redis state: { rung: 2, stop: entry * 1.04, banked: 33%,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trailing: 67% }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   WHY 33% AT +6%:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   33% of a 6% gain = 1.98% gain on the banked portion alone.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   This is 99% of the 2% daily target from just the banked portion.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   The remaining 67% trailing provides pure upside optionality.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RUNG 3: MOMENTUM CONTINUATION (Tighten Trail)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Trigger:     Price >= entry * 1.08 (i.e., +8% on 3x ETP)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Stop:        Ratchet to entry * 1.06 (lock +6% profit floor on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remaining 67%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                Trail: 2% below current high-water mark, whichever
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is higher.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Action:      No additional banking. Let the 67% trail run.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                The 2% ratchet trail means: if price reaches 108,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stop = 106.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                If price then reaches 110, stop ratchets to 107.8
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (110 * 0.98).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Risk:        Low. Worst case on trailing portion: exit at +6%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Rung 2 level).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Redis state: { rung: 3, stop: max(entry*1.06, hwm*0.98), banked:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 33%, trailing: 67% }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RUNG 4: EXTENDED MOVE (Tightest Trail)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Trigger:     Price >= entry * 1.10 (i.e., +10% on 3x ETP)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Stop:        Ratchet trail tightens to 1.5% below high-water
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mark.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                At +10%, stop = entry * 1.10 * 0.985 = entry *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.0835
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Action:      No additional banking. The 67% trail is capturing a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: genuine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                momentum event. These are rare (perhaps 1 in 15
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: winning trades)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                but account for 30-40% of total system profit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Risk:        Very low. Large profit locked in on trailing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: portion.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Redis state: { rung: 4, stop: max(prev_stop, hwm*0.985), banked:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 33%, trailing: 67% }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RUNG 5+: NO CEILING (Infinite Extension)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Trigger:     Price >= entry * 1.12, and beyond
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Stop:        Trail at 1.5% below high-water mark (same as Rung
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                NO additional tightening. The 1.5% trail is tight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enough.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Action:      Let it run. NO CEILING.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                Historical data shows 3x ETPs can move 15-25%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intraday on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                high-volatility days (earnings, macro shocks, short
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: squeezes).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                Capping at +10% or +12% would sacrifice these tail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: events.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Risk:        Negligible. Massive profit locked.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Redis state: { rung: 5, stop: max(prev_stop, hwm*0.985), banked:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 33%, trailing: 67% }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Profit Ladder State Transitions (ASCII Diagram)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   ENTRY ──[+1.5*ATR]──> RUNG 1 (BE) ──[+6%]──> RUNG 2 (BANK 33%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                   [+8%]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                  RUNG 3 (2% trail)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                   [+10%]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                  RUNG 4 (1.5%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trail)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                   [+12%+]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                        v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                                  RUNG 5+ (1.5%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trail, NO CEILING)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   At ANY rung, if stop is hit:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Rung 0: Full loss at -1R. Log and learn.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Rung 1: Breakeven exit. No P&L impact (minus spread).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Rung 2+: Profitable exit on trailing 67% at locked floor.
