   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ChandelierExit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Key methods:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: evaluate_rung_transition(position, current_price)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- checks if price has
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: crossed the next rung threshold
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compute_trailing_stop(rung, entry_price, high_water_mark)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- returns the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: current stop level
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: execute_bank(position, bank_pct)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- logs the partial close and updates Redis state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: persist_state(position_id, state_dict)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- writes to Redis with WAIT (v13.0 fix)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.5 Dynamic Heat Cap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Definition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Heat
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is the total capital at risk across all open positions for a single ticker. The heat cap prevents
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: over-concentration in any single name, which is critical for leveraged ETPs where a single gap-down can be 10-20%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on a 3x product.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Formula
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max_heat(ticker) = 0.03 * ADV_20d * price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ADV
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 20d = 20-day average daily volume (shares)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: price = current mid-price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 3% of ADV threshold ensures the position is small relative to daily turnover, preventing:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Market impact on entry (moving the price against ourselves)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Liquidity trap on exit (unable to exit at the trailing stop price)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Signaling risk (large orders visible in the order book)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scaling Behavior
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Account Equity | Max Position (from Kelly) | Heat Cap (QQQ3.L, ADV=500K, price=GBP 45) | Binding? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------------|--------------------------|-------------------------------------------|----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | GBP 10,000 | GBP 1,500 (15%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kelly) | GBP 675,000 | No -- heat cap is 450x the position. Irrelevant at this scale. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | GBP 50,000 | GBP 7,500 | GBP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 675,000 | No. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | GBP 100,000 | GBP 15,000 | GBP 675,000 | No. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | GBP 500,000 | GBP 75,000 | GBP 675,000 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Approaching
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- position is 11% of heat cap. Monitor. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | GBP 1,000,000 | GBP 150,000 | GBP 675,000 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Binding on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: some tickers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- smaller ETPs (MU2.L, TSM3.L) with lower ADV will hit heat cap before Kelly cap. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | GBP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5,000,000 | GBP 750,000 | GBP 675,000 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Binding
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- heat cap is the primary constraint. Must diversify across more
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tickers or accept reduced allocation. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key insight for current operations
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : At GBP 10,000, the heat cap is not a binding constraint. It exists as a safety
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rail for the compounding future when equity grows. The system must be designed for the GBP 500K+ world even
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: though it starts at GBP 10K.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For illiquid ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (e.g., MU2.L with ADV ~50K shares): max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heat = 0.03 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  50,000 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  GBP 20 = GBP 30,000. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: binds at approximately GBP 200K account equity. At that point, the system must either avoid MU2.L or accept
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reduced position sizing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6 Redis State Persistence Fix 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G-R2 ACCEPT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem Description
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gemini R2 identified a critical race condition in the profit ladder state management:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Timeline of failure:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.000s  Price crosses Rung 1 threshold (+1.5*ATR above entry)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.001s  ChandelierExit computes new stop = breakeven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.002s  Redis SET command issued for new stop level
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.003s  --- DOCKER RESTART OCCURS (e.g., health check failure,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OOM kill) ---
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.004s  Redis SET is in write buffer, NOT yet flushed to AOF
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.010s  Docker container restarts, Redis loads from last AOF sync
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.011s  Position state restored with OLD stop (Rung 0, -1R below
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entry)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.012s  Price reverses, old stop (-1R) is hit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T+0.013s  Full loss taken on a trade that SHOULD have been at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: breakeven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Result: The system takes a -1R loss on a trade that had already
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reached Rung 1.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is a STATE LOSS BUG, not a trading logic bug.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Root Cause
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Redis AOF (Append Only File) persistence uses 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fsync
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  policies:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: always
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : fsync after every write (safe but slow, ~1ms per write)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: everysec
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : fsync once per second (default, can lose up to 1 second of data)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : OS decides when to fsync (can lose minutes of data)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The current configuration uses 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: everysec
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , meaning any Docker restart within 1 second of a state write can lose
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that write.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix: Redis WAIT Command
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WAIT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  command blocks until the write has been acknowledged by the specified number of replicas. In a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: single-instance deployment (which NZT-48 uses), WAIT with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: numreplicas=0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  combined with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: appendfsync
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: always
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for critical writes ensures durability.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: However, since we are on a single Redis instance (no replicas), the correct fix is a two-part approach:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Part 1: Use a Lua script for atomic rung transitions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- scripts/rung_transition.lua
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- Atomic rung transition: update stop, rung, and timestamp in one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- KEYS[1] = position hash key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- ARGV[1] = new rung number
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- ARGV[2] = new stop level
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- ARGV[3] = banked percentage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- ARGV[4] = trailing percentage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- ARGV[5] = timestamp
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: redis.call('HMSET', KEYS[1],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'rung', ARGV[1],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'stop', ARGV[2],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'banked_pct', ARGV[3],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'trail_pct', ARGV[4],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'last_rung_change', ARGV[5]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -- Force AOF rewrite of this critical state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: redis.call('BGSAVE')
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: return redis.call('HGETALL', KEYS[1])
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Part 2: Verify persistence before confirming rung transition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # In core/state_manager.py, method persist_rung_transition()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: def persist_rung_transition(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     self,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     position_id: str,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     new_rung: int,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     new_stop: float,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     banked_pct: float,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     trail_pct: float
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) -> bool:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Atomically persist a rung transition to Redis with durability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: guarantee.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Returns True only if the state is confirmed persisted.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Uses Lua script for atomicity + BGSAVE for durability.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     On failure, the position retains its PREVIOUS rung state (safe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: default).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     timestamp = datetime.utcnow().isoformat()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     key = f"position:{position_id}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     try:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         result = self.redis.eval(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             self.rung_transition_script,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             1,  # number of keys
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             key,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             str(new_rung),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             str(new_stop),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             str(banked_pct),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             str(trail_pct),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             timestamp
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         # Verify the write by reading back
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         stored_rung = self.redis.hget(key, 'rung')
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if stored_rung != str(new_rung):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             logger.critical(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"RUNG PERSISTENCE FAILURE: position={position_id},
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"expected_rung={new_rung},
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stored_rung={stored_rung}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return False
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         logger.info(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"Rung transition persisted: position={position_id}, "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"rung={new_rung}, stop={new_stop},
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: banked={banked_pct}%, "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"trail={trail_pct}%"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return True
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     except redis.RedisError as e:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         logger.critical(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"Redis error during rung transition:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position={position_id}, "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"error={e}. Position retains previous rung state."
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return False
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Part 3: Docker Compose configuration update
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # In docker-compose.yml, redis service
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nzt48-redis:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   image: redis:7-alpine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   command: >
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     redis-server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     --requirepass nzt48redis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     --appendonly yes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     --appendfsync always
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     --save 60 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     --save 300 100
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   volumes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     - redis_data:/data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   restart: unless-stopped
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: appendfsync always
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  setting ensures every write is flushed to disk before Redis acknowledges it. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: performance cost (~1ms per write) is negligible for a system that executes at most a few trades per day.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Part 4: Startup recovery check
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: On container startup, the engine must verify all active position states:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # In main.py, startup sequence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: def verify_position_states_on_startup():
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     On startup, verify all active positions have consistent state.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     If any position has a rung > 0 but a stop below breakeven,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     this indicates a persistence failure. Force stop to breakeven.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     active_positions = state_manager.get_all_active_positions()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     for pos in active_positions:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if pos['rung'] >= 1 and pos['stop'] < pos['entry_price']:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             logger.critical(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"STATE INCONSISTENCY DETECTED on startup: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"position={pos['id']}, rung={pos['rung']}, "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"stop={pos['stop']}, entry={pos['entry_price']}. "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"Forcing stop to breakeven."
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             state_manager.persist_rung_transition(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 pos['id'],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 new_rung=pos['rung'],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 new_stop=pos['entry_price'] + pos['spread_cost'],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 banked_pct=pos.get('banked_pct', 0),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 trail_pct=pos.get('trail_pct', 100)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SECTION 5: THE OUROBOROS -- Self-Learning AI + Risk Shell
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Ouroboros (self-eating serpent) represents the system
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s ability to learn from its own outcomes and continuously
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recalibrate. This section covers the ML meta-model improvements, portfolio-level risk management, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime-conditional position sizing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.1 Current ML State (Verified from Codebase)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The ML meta-model acts as a binary gate on trade signals. It does not generate signals -- it filters them. This is the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: De Prado (2018) meta-labeling paradigm: the primary model (S15 + gauntlet) generates candidates, and the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: meta-model predicts whether each candidate will be profitable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Current Architecture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PRIMARY MODEL (S15 DailyTarget)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Signal candidate with features
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ML META-MODEL (binary gate)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     +--> P(profit) >= threshold --> PASS to ExecutionPlanner
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     +--> P(profit) < threshold  --> REJECT, log reason
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: META-MODEL INTERNALS:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Ensemble: LightGBM (weight 0.55) + XGBoost (weight 0.45)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     LightGBM:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         n_estimators=200, max_depth=6, learning_rate=0.05
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         min_child_samples=20, subsample=0.8, colsample_bytree=0.8
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     XGBoost:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         n_estimators=150, max_depth=5, learning_rate=0.05
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         min_child_weight=10, subsample=0.8, colsample_bytree=0.8
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Ensemble prediction:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         P(profit) = 0.55 * P_lgbm + 0.45 * P_xgb
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Current features (14):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         1.  atr_ratio_15m        (ATR_15m / ATR_1h)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         2.  spread_pct           (bid-ask spread as % of mid)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         3.  volume_ratio         (current volume / ADV_20d)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         4.  rsi_14               (14-period RSI on 15m bars)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         5.  macd_histogram       (MACD histogram on 15m bars)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         6.  obv_slope            (OBV linear regression slope, 20
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: periods)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         7.  regime_code          (HMM regime as integer 0-6)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         8.  vix_level            (VIX index level)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         9.  sector_momentum      (sector-level 5d momentum)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         10. correlation_to_qqq   (rolling 20d correlation to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: QQQ3.L)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         11. hour_of_day          (fractional hour, e.g., 10.5 =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 10:30)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         12. day_of_week          (0=Mon, 4=Fri)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         13. confidence           *** FEATURE LEAKAGE -- MUST REMOVE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ***
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         14. days_since_last_trade (calendar days since last trade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on this ticker)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Training data: 413+ trades from paper trading
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Retrain trigger: weekly OR 50 new trades (whichever comes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: first)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Validation: 5-fold stratified cross-validation (MUST upgrade to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: walk-forward)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     SHAP stability filter (Gu, Kelly & Xiu 2020):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         After each retrain, compute SHAP values for all features.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         If a feature's mean |SHAP| drops below 0.01 for 3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consecutive retrains,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         flag for review (but do not auto-remove -- human reviews
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quarterly).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     CUSUM alpha reaper (Page 1954):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Monitors cumulative sum of trade outcomes (win=+1,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loss=-1).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         If CUSUM exceeds threshold (3.0), the strategy is flagged
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: as decaying.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Current state: ON, threshold=3.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.2 ML Improvements Required
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: M-01: Remove Feature Leakage (CRITICAL -- Priority P0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Feature 13 (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) is the composite confidence score output by the signal generation pipeline.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This score is computed AFTER the signal is generated, using information that includes partial outputs from the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gauntlet gates. Including it as an ML feature creates circular dependency:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Signal pipeline computes confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     --> confidence is input to ML model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         --> ML model's prediction influences whether the trade is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: taken
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             --> trade outcome is the label that trains the ML model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 --> ML model learns to weight confidence heavily
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     --> confidence becomes a proxy for "did the ML
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model agree?"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                         --> CIRCULAR. The model is partially
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: predicting itself.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is textbook feature leakage as described by De Prado (2018, Chapter 7). The confidence feature likely inflates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: apparent AUC by 3-5% because it encodes information about the label.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Remove 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  from the feature vector. Replace with three orthogonal features that capture the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: information 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  was proxying:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: REMOVE:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     13. confidence              (LEAKAGE)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ADD:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     13. raw_indicator_count     (integer count of indicators
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agreeing with signal direction)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                  Range: 0-12. Pure signal, no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: circular dependency.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     14. spread_bps              (raw bid-ask spread in basis points
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at signal time)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                  Replaces the spread component
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: embedded in confidence.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     15. time_since_regime_change_hours  (hours since last HMM
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime transition)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                  Captures regime freshness -- early
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime signals
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                  may be less reliable than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: established regimes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: New feature count
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 15 (was 14, net +1 after removing confidence and adding 3).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Validation requirement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : After removing confidence and retraining, AUC may DROP by 3-5%. This is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: EXPECTED and CORRECT. The model was overfitting to the leaked feature. The true out-of-sample AUC will be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more reliable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/ml_meta_model.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , method 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _prepare_features()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Remove 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from the feature list. Add the three new features. Retrain immediately with the next 50-trade batch.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: M-02: Class Weight Balancing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The training data is likely imbalanced (more winning trades than losing trades, or vice versa, depending
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on the strategy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s base rate). Without class weighting, the ML model biases toward the majority class, which means it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: either over-accepts (if wins are majority) or over-rejects (if losses are majority).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Add 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: class_weight='balanced'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to both models:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # LightGBM
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lgbm_params = {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'objective': 'binary',
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'is_unbalance': True,  # LightGBM equivalent of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: class_weight='balanced'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     # ... other params unchanged
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # XGBoost
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: xgb_params = {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'objective': 'binary:logistic',
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'scale_pos_weight': n_negative / n_positive,  # XGBoost
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: equivalent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     # ... other params unchanged
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expected impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Improved precision-recall balance. The model should reject more marginal trades (reducing false
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: positives) while maintaining recall on high-quality setups.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: M-03: Walk-Forward Validation (Replacing 5-Fold Stratified CV)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Standard k-fold cross-validation randomly shuffles the data, violating temporal ordering. A model trained
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on data from trade #300 can be validated on trade #100, which means it has seen the future. For financial time
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: series, this inflates performance estimates and masks regime-dependent overfitting.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Implement expanding-window walk-forward validation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CURRENT (v12.0): 5-Fold Stratified CV
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Fold 1: Train on trades {2,3,4,5}, test on {1}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Fold 2: Train on trades {1,3,4,5}, test on {2}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ... (temporal ordering destroyed)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NEW (v13.0): Expanding-Window Walk-Forward
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Split 1: Train on trades [1..248],   Validate on [249..330],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Test on [331..413]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Split 2: Train on trades [1..290],   Validate on [291..370],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Test on [371..413]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Split 3: Train on trades [1..330],   Validate on [331..390],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Test on [391..413]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     General rule:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Train:    60% of available data (expanding from left)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Validate: 20% (hyperparameter tuning, early stopping)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Test:     20% (final performance estimate, NEVER used for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tuning)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Report rolling AUC:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       For each walk-forward split, record test AUC.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       If test AUC trends downward across splits, the model is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decaying.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       If test AUC variance > 0.10 across splits, the model is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime-sensitive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/ml_meta_model.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , method 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _validate_model()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Replace 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with custom 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WalkForwardSplit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  class.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: class WalkForwardSplit:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Expanding-window walk-forward cross-validation for time series.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Respects temporal ordering. Never uses future data for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: training.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def __init__(self, n_splits=3, train_pct=0.6, val_pct=0.2):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         self.n_splits = n_splits
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         self.train_pct = train_pct
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         self.val_pct = val_pct
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def split(self, X):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         n = len(X)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         test_pct = 1.0 - self.train_pct - self.val_pct
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         for i in range(self.n_splits):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             # Expand training window
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             extra = int(i * (n * test_pct) / self.n_splits)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             train_end = int(n * self.train_pct) + extra
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             val_end = train_end + int(n * self.val_pct)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             train_idx = list(range(0, train_end))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             val_idx = list(range(train_end, min(val_end, n)))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             test_idx = list(range(val_end, n))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             if len(test_idx) < 10:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 continue  # Skip if test set too small
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             yield train_idx, val_idx, test_idx
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Reporting
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : After each retrain, log the following to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data/logs/ml_walkforward.log
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "retrain_timestamp": "2026-03-04T14:30:00Z",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "n_trades": 413,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "splits": [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         {"split": 1, "train_size": 248, "val_size": 82,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "test_size": 83,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          "test_auc": 0.612, "test_precision": 0.58, "test_recall":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.65},
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         {"split": 2, "train_size": 290, "val_size": 80,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "test_size": 43,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          "test_auc": 0.634, "test_precision": 0.61, "test_recall":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.63},
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         {"split": 3, "train_size": 330, "val_size": 60,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "test_size": 23,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          "test_auc": 0.645, "test_precision": 0.63, "test_recall":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.60}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ],
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "mean_test_auc": 0.630,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "auc_trend": "improving",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "auc_variance": 0.017
