   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: M-04: Pattern x Regime Interaction Tracking
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : A candlestick pattern (e.g., bullish engulfing) may be highly predictive in TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: meaningless in RANGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BOUND. The current system treats pattern signals as regime-independent, which dilutes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: their informational value.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Maintain a pattern-regime interaction matrix that tracks win rates conditionally.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data/pattern_regime_matrix.json structure:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "bullish_engulfing": {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         "TRENDING_UP_STRONG":   { "wins": 23, "losses": 8,  "wr":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.742 },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         "TRENDING_UP_MOD":      { "wins": 15, "losses": 12, "wr":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.556 },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         "RANGE_BOUND":          { "wins": 5,  "losses": 9,  "wr":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.357 },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         "TRENDING_DOWN_MOD":    { "wins": 2,  "losses": 7,  "wr":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.222 },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         "TRENDING_DOWN_STRONG": { "wins": 0,  "losses": 3,  "wr":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.000 },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         "RISK_OFF":             { "wins": 0,  "losses": 1,  "wr":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.000 },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         "SHOCK":                { "wins": 0,  "losses": 0,  "wr":
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: null  }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "hammer": { ... },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "morning_star": { ... },
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ...
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Usage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : When a signal includes a pattern component, multiply the pattern
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s contribution to the signal score by the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime-conditional win rate. If the regime-conditional sample is below 10 trades, fall back to the unconditional win
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rate with a 0.5x stranger penalty.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Update frequency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : After every trade outcome. The matrix is append-only and never reset (rolling window handled
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by the ML retrain, not by the matrix itself).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: M-05: CUSUM Alpha Reaper -- Verification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The CUSUM (Cumulative Sum) alpha reaper is already implemented in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/ml_meta_model.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Based on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Page (1954), it monitors the cumulative sum of standardized trade outcomes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: S_t = max(0, S_{t-1} + (outcome_t - mu_0))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where mu
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0 is the expected outcome under the null hypothesis (strategy is performing at baseline). When S
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exceeds the threshold (currently 3.0), the alpha reaper triggers a flag.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Current implementation status
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : ON, threshold = 3.0.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Verification required
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : During the next 63 MTRL paper trading days, verify that:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CUSUM correctly triggers when a deliberate 10-trade losing streak is simulated.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CUSUM correctly resets after the strategy resumes normal performance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The threshold of 3.0 is calibrated to the system
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s actual outcome distribution (not just assumed).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : No code changes needed. Add CUSUM verification to the Sprint 4 test plan.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.3 Portfolio CDaR Circuit Breaker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theoretical Foundation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CVaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Conditional Value-at-Risk, Rockafellar 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Uryasev 2000): Measures the expected loss in the worst
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: alpha-percentile of outcomes. Unlike VaR, CVaR is coherent (subadditive) and captures tail risk. For a single trade,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CVaR answers: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If this trade goes badly, how badly?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Conditional Drawdown-at-Risk, Chekhlov, Uryasev 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zabarankin 2005): Extends CVaR to drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: processes. CVaR treats each trade independently; CDaR captures the serial dependence in drawdowns. A sequence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of three -1R losses is worse than three isolated -1R losses because of psychological impact, margin erosion, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compounding damage. CDaR answers: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If we enter a drawdown, how deep will it get?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The distinction is critical for a leveraged ETP strategy where losses compound: a -3% loss followed by a -3% loss is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not -6% but -5.91% (and on a 3x ETP, the tracking error makes this worse). CDaR captures this path-dependent risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Three-Tier Risk Architecture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TIER 1: Per-Trade Gate (CVaR)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Computed BEFORE entry, using the proposed position size and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: historical
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     outcome distribution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Formula:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         CVaR_95 = E[Loss | Loss > VaR_95]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Where VaR_95 is the 5th percentile of the P&L distribution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         (i.e., the loss that is exceeded only 5% of the time).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     RULE:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         IF CVaR_95 > 3% of current equity --> BLOCK this entry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Example at GBP 10,000 equity:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         CVaR_95 > GBP 300 --> BLOCK.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         For a 3x ETP with 3% stop and 15% Kelly:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             max loss = GBP 10,000 * 0.15 * 0.03 = GBP 45. CVaR ~
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GBP 55 (with slippage).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             55/10,000 = 0.55%. PASS.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         For a 5x ETP with 5% stop and 20% Kelly (hypothetical
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: aggressive sizing):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             max loss = GBP 10,000 * 0.20 * 0.05 = GBP 100. CVaR ~
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GBP 140.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             140/10,000 = 1.4%. PASS (but close to warning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TIER 2: Portfolio Circuit Breaker (CDaR)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Computed continuously, using the trailing equity curve.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Formula:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         CDaR_95 = E[Drawdown | Drawdown > DDaR_95]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Where DDaR_95 is the drawdown that is exceeded only 5% of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the time,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         computed over all drawdown paths in the lookback window (60
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trading days).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     RULES:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         IF CDaR_95 > 5% of peak equity:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             --> HALT ALL new entries
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             --> Tighten ALL existing stops to 0.5 * ATR (emergency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trailing)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             --> Log P0 alert: "CDaR CIRCUIT BREAKER: portfolio
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drawdown tail risk at {CDaR_95:.2%}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             --> Cooldown: 24 hours minimum before new entries
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: permitted
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             --> Re-entry requires CDaR_95 < 3% (hysteresis to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: prevent oscillation)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     The 5% threshold at GBP 10,000 = GBP 500 drawdown in the tail.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     At GBP 100,000 = GBP 5,000. At GBP 1,000,000 = GBP 50,000.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     The threshold is in percentage terms and scales with equity,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which is correct.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TIER 3: Incremental CVaR (iCVaR) Veto
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Computed BEFORE adding a new position to an existing portfolio.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Formula:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         iCVaR = CVaR_95(portfolio + new_position) -
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CVaR_95(portfolio)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     RULE:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         IF iCVaR > 0.5% of equity --> VETO this entry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     This prevents adding a correlated position that pushes the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: portfolio's
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     tail risk beyond acceptable bounds, even if the position
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: individually
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     passes the Tier 1 gate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Example:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Portfolio holds QQQ3.L (long 3x Nasdaq).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Signal fires for NVD3.L (long 3x Nvidia).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Correlation(QQQ3.L, NVD3.L) = 0.85.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         CVaR_95(QQQ3.L alone) = 1.2%.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         CVaR_95(QQQ3.L + NVD3.L) = 2.8% (NOT 2.4% -- correlation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amplifies tail).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         iCVaR = 2.8% - 1.2% = 1.6%.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         1.6% > 0.5% --> VETO NVD3.L entry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # In risk_officer/cdar_breaker.py (new module)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from riskfolio import RiskFunctions  # Riskfolio-Lib v7.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: class CDaRCircuitBreaker:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Portfolio-level drawdown risk monitor using CDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (Chekhlov, Uryasev & Zabarankin 2005).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Implements three-tier risk architecture:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Tier 1: Per-trade CVaR gate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Tier 2: Portfolio CDaR circuit breaker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       Tier 3: Incremental CVaR veto
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def __init__(self, equity_series: pd.Series, alpha: float =
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.05):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Args:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             equity_series: Daily equity curve (index=date,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: values=equity)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             alpha: Confidence level (0.05 = 95th percentile)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         self.equity = equity_series
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         self.alpha = alpha
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         self.returns = equity_series.pct_change().dropna()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def compute_cvar(self, returns: pd.Series) -> float:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """Per-trade CVaR at (1-alpha) confidence."""
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         var = returns.quantile(self.alpha)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         cvar = returns[returns <= var].mean()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return abs(cvar)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def compute_cdar(self, lookback_days: int = 60) -> float:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Portfolio CDaR using Riskfolio-Lib.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Captures serial dependence in drawdowns.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         recent = self.returns.tail(lookback_days)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         cum_returns = (1 + recent).cumprod()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         running_max = cum_returns.cummax()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         drawdowns = (cum_returns - running_max) / running_max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         # CDaR = expected drawdown in worst alpha-percentile of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drawdown paths
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         dd_threshold = drawdowns.quantile(self.alpha)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         cdar = drawdowns[drawdowns <= dd_threshold].mean()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return abs(cdar)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def check_tier1(self, position_cvar: float, equity: float) ->
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tuple:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """Tier 1: Per-trade CVaR gate. Returns (pass: bool,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reason: str)."""
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         pct = position_cvar / equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if pct > 0.03:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return False, f"CVaR gate: {pct:.2%} > 3% threshold"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return True, "CVaR gate: PASS"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def check_tier2(self, equity: float, peak_equity: float) ->
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tuple:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """Tier 2: Portfolio CDaR circuit breaker."""
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         cdar = self.compute_cdar()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if cdar > 0.05:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return False, (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"CDaR CIRCUIT BREAKER: tail drawdown risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {cdar:.2%} > 5%. "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"HALT ALL entries. Tighten stops to 0.5*ATR. "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"Re-entry requires CDaR < 3%."
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return True, f"CDaR gate: {cdar:.2%} (within 5% threshold)"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     def check_tier3(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         self,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         portfolio_returns: pd.Series,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         combined_returns: pd.Series,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         equity: float
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ) -> tuple:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         """Tier 3: Incremental CVaR veto."""
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         cvar_before = self.compute_cvar(portfolio_returns)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         cvar_after = self.compute_cvar(combined_returns)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         icvar = cvar_after - cvar_before
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         if icvar > 0.005:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             return False, (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"iCVaR veto: adding position increases tail risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 f"{icvar:.2%} > 0.5% threshold"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return True, f"iCVaR gate: incremental risk {icvar:.2%}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (within 0.5% threshold)"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dependency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pip install Riskfolio-Lib>=7.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Add to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: requirements.txt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . The library provides
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optimized CDaR computation with the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rm='CDaR'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  risk measure parameter for portfolio optimization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.4 Anti-Correlation Monitoring
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Portfolio Correlation Brake
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Leveraged ETPs on the same underlying sector (e.g., QQQ3.L and NVD3.L both track tech-heavy indices) exhibit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: high correlation. When multiple correlated positions are open simultaneously, a single adverse event (e.g., Nasdaq
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gap-down) hits all of them, creating a cascading loss that exceeds the CDaR model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s assumptions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Correlation estimation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Use Ledoit-Wolf shrinkage estimator (Ledoit 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Wolf 2004) to estimate the correlation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: matrix. Shrinkage is essential because with 12-18 tickers and potentially short lookback windows (60 days), the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sample correlation matrix is noisy and can be singular.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from sklearn.covariance import LedoitWolf
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: def compute_shrunk_correlation(returns_df: pd.DataFrame) ->
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pd.DataFrame:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Compute Ledoit-Wolf shrinkage correlation matrix.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     More stable than sample correlation for small-N, large-p
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regimes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     lw = LedoitWolf().fit(returns_df.dropna())
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     cov = lw.covariance_
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     std = np.sqrt(np.diag(cov))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     corr = cov / np.outer(std, std)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     return pd.DataFrame(corr, index=returns_df.columns,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: columns=returns_df.columns)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : If 3 or more pairs in the portfolio have correlation > 0.70, cap active positions at 1 (single position only). This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: prevents the scenario where the system holds QQQ3.L, NVD3.L, and GPT3.L simultaneously -- all three would
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: move in lockstep on a tech selloff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: IF count(pairwise_correlations > 0.70) >= 3:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     max_positions = 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Log: "CORRELATION BRAKE: {n} pairs above 0.70, capping to 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ELSE:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     max_positions = standard_limit (from DynamicSizer)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Anti-Cascade Stop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : If the market gaps against us, multiple stops can trigger in rapid succession. Each stop hit generates a sell
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: order, which can further depress the price (especially in illiquid ETPs), causing the next stop to trigger, and so on.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is a cascade failure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : If 3 or more stops are hit within a 15-minute window, trigger a P0 HALT with a 30-minute cooldown.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: IF count(stops_hit, window=15min) >= 3:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     HALT ALL trading for 30 minutes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Cancel all pending orders.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Log P0 alert: "ANTI-CASCADE: {n} stops hit in 15 minutes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                    Cooldown until {resume_time}."
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     After cooldown:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         Re-evaluate all remaining positions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         If CDaR_95 > 5%: extend halt indefinitely (Tier 2 takes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: over).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         If CDaR_95 <= 5%: resume normal operations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Correlation Escalation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : If 3 or more P1 alerts fire within 15 minutes, auto-escalate to P0.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: P1 alerts include:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     - Single stop hit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     - Spread widening above threshold
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     - Volume drop below minimum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     - Regime transition detected
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     - CUSUM warning (below threshold but trending)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: IF count(P1_alerts, window=15min) >= 3:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ESCALATE to P0.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Trigger the anti-cascade stop protocol.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Log: "CORRELATION ESCALATION: {n} P1 alerts in 15 minutes -->
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: P0"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Multiple simultaneous P1 alerts are rarely independent. They typically indicate a systemic event (macro
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shock, flash crash, liquidity withdrawal) that justifies a full halt.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.5 Regime-Conditional Kelly (Hamilton 1989 HMM Framework)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Background
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Kelly criterion (Kelly 1956) computes the optimal fraction of capital to risk:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f* = (p * b - q) / b
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where p = probability of winning, b = odds (avg
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: win / avg
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loss), q = 1 - p.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: However, f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  assumes stationary statistics -- the win rate and payoff ratio are constant. In reality, these vary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dramatically across market regimes. A strategy that wins 65% of the time in TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG may win
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only 38% in RANGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BOUND.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regime-Conditional Kelly computes a separate f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for each HMM regime and applies regime-specific multipliers to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: prevent over-sizing in adverse regimes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regime Multipliers (v13.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | HMM Regime | Multiplier (v12.0) | Multiplier (v13.0) | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------------|--------------------|--------------------|-----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG | 0.6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Unchanged. Strong trend with momentum confirmation. Highest allocation but still below full Kelly (overbetting
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: protection on levered instruments). |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MOD | 0.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Unchanged. Moderate trend.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Reduced from strong because trend conviction is lower. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | RANGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BOUND | 0.3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Unchanged.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Momentum strategies have lowest edge in range-bound markets. Win rate drops to ~45-50%, justifying significant
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reduction. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MOD | 0.4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Unchanged. Counter-trend bounces can be caught, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the base direction is against us. 0.4 is appropriate for a momentum-long system in a mild downtrend. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
