   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bleeding capital for no expected edge. Zero allocation is correct. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | SHOCK | 0.0 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.0 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Unchanged. No
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trading during shock events (flash crash, circuit breaker, gap > 5%). |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Change Detail: RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF Multiplier (0.2 --> 0.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is the most significant change in Section 5. The argument chain:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Empirical observation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : In RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF regimes (as classified by the HMM on historical data), the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: momentum strategy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s win rate drops to 32-38% across all tickers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kelly at WR = 35%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = (0.35 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2.0 - 0.65) / 2.0 = 0.025 (2.5% of capital). Already tiny.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Apply 0.2 multiplier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 0.2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0.025 = 0.005 (0.5% of capital, i.e., GBP 50 at GBP 10K).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Net of spread
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : GBP 50 position on a 3x ETP with 40 bps spread = GBP 0.20 spread cost. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expected profit on a GBP 50 position with 35% WR and 2:1 R:R is approximately GBP 0.25. Net
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expected value: GBP 0.05.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Conclusion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Trading GBP 50 positions to make GBP 0.05 expected profit while incurring system
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: complexity, state management, and psychological cost is not rational. Zero allocation is correct.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF regime is now a pure observation period: the system watches, learns, and waits for regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transition. No capital is deployed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Removing the 0.75% Hard Cap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: v12.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : A hard cap of 0.75% of equity per trade was applied as a safety net, regardless of regime-Kelly output.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: v13.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The hard cap is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: removed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The regime-conditional Kelly with portfolio heat as a safety net provides sufficient protection:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regime-Kelly self-regulates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:44,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : In adverse regimes, the multiplier (0.0-0.3) already reduces position
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sizes far below the 0.75% cap. The cap only binds in favorable regimes (TRENDING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STRONG at 0.6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ), where it artificially constrains the system
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s best opportunities.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Portfolio heat cap (3%) is the safety net
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heat constraint (Section 4.5) ensures no single
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ticker can consume more than 3% of ADV. Combined with the Bayesian stranger penalty (Section
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2), this provides adequate per-position protection.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CDaR circuit breaker (5%) is the portfolio-level safety net
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : If regime-Kelly oversizes and the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: market moves against us, the CDaR breaker (Section 5.3) halts all trading before the drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: becomes existential.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 0.75% cap was calibrated for a system WITHOUT these safeguards
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : When it was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: introduced, the CDaR breaker and Bayesian stranger penalty did not exist. Now that they do, the cap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is redundant and harmful (it caps upside without meaningful downside protection).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Constraint
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Regime-Kelly requires a minimum of 30 trades per regime for stable f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  estimation. Until this threshold
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is met for a given regime, use the global (regime-unconditional) f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with a 0.5x stranger penalty applied to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: IF trades_in_regime < 30:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     f*_regime = f*_global * 0.5 * regime_multiplier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Log: "Regime-Kelly: insufficient data for {regime} ({n} trades
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: < 30).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           Using global f* with 0.5x penalty."
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ELSE:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     f*_regime = f*_regime_specific * regime_multiplier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # In core/dynamic_sizer.py, method _compute_regime_kelly()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: REGIME_MULTIPLIERS = {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'TRENDING_UP_STRONG':   0.6,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'TRENDING_UP_MOD':      0.5,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'RANGE_BOUND':          0.3,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'TRENDING_DOWN_MOD':    0.4,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'TRENDING_DOWN_STRONG': 0.3,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'RISK_OFF':             0.0,  # v13.0: changed from 0.2 [G-R2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ACCEPT]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     'SHOCK':                0.0,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MIN_TRADES_PER_REGIME = 30
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: def _compute_regime_kelly(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     self,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     regime: str,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     global_f_star: float,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     regime_trade_count: int,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     regime_win_rate: float,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     regime_avg_win: float,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     regime_avg_loss: float
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) -> float:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Compute regime-conditional Kelly fraction.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Falls back to global f* with 0.5x penalty if insufficient
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     regime-specific data (< 30 trades).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     multiplier = REGIME_MULTIPLIERS.get(regime, 0.3)  # Default to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cautious
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     if multiplier == 0.0:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         logger.info(f"Regime-Kelly: {regime} has zero multiplier.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No allocation.")
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return 0.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     if regime_trade_count < MIN_TRADES_PER_REGIME:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         f_star = global_f_star * 0.5 * multiplier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         logger.info(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"Regime-Kelly: {regime} has {regime_trade_count}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trades "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"(< {MIN_TRADES_PER_REGIME}). Using global
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f*={global_f_star:.4f} "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             f"* 0.5 * {multiplier} = {f_star:.4f}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return f_star
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     # Compute regime-specific Kelly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     if regime_avg_loss == 0:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return 0.0  # No losses recorded -- insufficient data for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kelly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     b = regime_avg_win / regime_avg_loss  # Odds
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     p = regime_win_rate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     q = 1.0 - p
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     f_star_regime = max(0.0, (p * b - q) / b)  # Kelly formula,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: floored at 0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     f_star = f_star_regime * multiplier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     logger.info(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         f"Regime-Kelly: {regime} (n={regime_trade_count}), "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         f"WR={p:.2%}, b={b:.2f}, raw_f*={f_star_regime:.4f}, "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         f"multiplier={multiplier}, final_f*={f_star:.4f}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     return f_star
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 5 Summary: Risk Shell Architecture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     +-----------------------------------+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |     OUROBOROS RISK SHELL           |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 1: ML Meta-Model Gate      |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    15 features, walk-forward CV   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    De Prado meta-labeling          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 2: Regime-Conditional Kelly |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    HMM regime detection            |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    Per-regime f* with multipliers  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    RISK_OFF = 0.0 (no trading)    |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 3: Bayesian Stranger Penalty|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    kappa(n, DSR) continuous        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    n_0 = 50, lambda = 0.5         |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 4: CVaR Per-Trade Gate      |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    CVaR_95 > 3% equity = BLOCK    |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 5: iCVaR Portfolio Gate     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    iCVaR > 0.5% equity = VETO     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 6: CDaR Circuit Breaker     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    CDaR_95 > 5% = HALT ALL        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    Re-entry at CDaR < 3%          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 7: Correlation Brake        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    3+ pairs > 0.70 = 1 position   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 8: Anti-Cascade Stop        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    3 stops in 15min = HALT 30min  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 9: CUSUM Alpha Reaper       |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    Strategy decay detection        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    Threshold = 3.0                 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |  Layer 10: Portfolio Heat Cap      |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |    3% of ADV_20d per ticker        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     |                                   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     +-----------------------------------+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     A signal must pass ALL 10 layers to reach execution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Any single layer veto = signal rejected.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     No override. No manual bypass. No exceptions.
