   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SECTION 6: RISK ARCHITECTURE — 15-Control Defence Matrix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The NZT-48 risk framework is a defence-in-depth architecture. No single control is trusted alone. All 15 controls
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operate independently and concurrently — any one can HALT or VETO a trade regardless of signal strength. Controls
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are grouped into legacy (verified in production code) and new (added in v12.0-v13.0 based on institutional audit and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gemini R2 adversarial review).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Existing Controls (Verified in Code)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-01: Five Independent Circuit Breakers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Breaker | Trigger Condition | Action Taken |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------|-------------------|--------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Drawdown | Portfolio DD
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exceeds threshold (2% daily / 5% weekly / 15% total) | HALT all new entries. Existing positions retain stops but no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: new risk added. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | VIX | VIX exceeds regime-adjusted threshold | Reduce position sizing or HALT depending on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: severity. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Correlation | Cross-asset correlation spike (contagion detection) | Reduce concurrent positions to 1. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Streak | Consecutive losing trades exceed threshold | Force cool-down period, reduce size on next entry. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Black
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Swan | Intraday move exceeds 3-sigma on any held instrument | Immediate HALT, flatten discretionary positions,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: notify P0. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Independent circuit breakers prevent single-point-of-failure in risk management. Each monitors a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: different failure mode. Academic basis: Danielsson et al. (2001), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: An Academic Response to Basel II
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — layered risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: controls outperform monolithic VaR gates.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-02: Immutable Risk Rules
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Parameter | Value | Override Permitted |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-----------|-------|--------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Max risk per trade | 0.75% of equity |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NO |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Daily loss halt | 2% of equity | NO |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Weekly loss halt | 5% of equity | NO |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Total drawdown halt | 15% of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: equity | NO |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Any trade that would violate these limits is rejected at the DynamicSizer level before order generation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Trade is silently vetoed. No override mechanism exists. These values are hardcoded, not configurable via
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: settings.yaml.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Fixed fractional position sizing with hard stops prevents ruin. The 0.75% per-trade limit ensures survival
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of 133 consecutive losers before reaching 15% total DD — a statistical impossibility for any strategy with edge.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic basis: Kelly (1956), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A New Interpretation of Information Rate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; Van Tharp (2006), position sizing as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: primary determinant of system performance; Ralph Vince (1990), optimal f and the danger of over-betting.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-03: Emotional Firewall (12 Blocked Patterns)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The emotional firewall pattern-matches against 12 specific behavioural signatures that indicate revenge
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trading, tilt, FOMO, or irrational override attempts. These include:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rapid re-entry after stop-out (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 min)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Size increase after losing trade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Manual override of automated stop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Entry against active regime signal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Multiple entries in same ticker within session
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Entry during circuit breaker cool-down
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  7 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Increasing frequency of trades after drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  8 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Correlated re-entry (entering a correlated instrument after stop)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  9 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Late-session FOMO entry (after 16:00 UK)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  10 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Revenge sizing (position > 1.5x normal after loss)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  11 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ignoring spread veto (manual attempt to bypass R-11)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  12 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Weekend/overnight hold increase during drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Pattern detected → entry BLOCKED, Telegram P1 alert sent with pattern name, 15-minute cool-down
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enforced.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Behavioural finance research shows that post-loss decision-making quality degrades sharply. Academic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: basis: Kahneman 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tversky (1979), Prospect Theory — loss aversion drives irrational risk-seeking after losses; Odean
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (1998), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Are Investors Reluctant to Realize Their Losses?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — disposition effect empirically demonstrated.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-04: Six-Level Drawdown Recovery Cascade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Level | DD Range | Position Cap | Size Multiplier | Max Heat | Action |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------|----------|-------------|-----------------|----------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Green | 0% to -2% | 3 positions | 1.0x | 3.0% | Normal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operations |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Yellow | -2% to -4% | 2 positions | 0.75x | 2.0% | Reduced aggression |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Orange | -4% to -6% | 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: position | 0.50x | 1.5% | Conservative only |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Red | -6% to -8% | 1 position | 0.25x | 0.75% | Survival mode, A-team
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signals only |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Critical | -8% to -10% | 0 new entries | 0.0x | 0.0% | HALT all new entries, manage exits only |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Emergency | -10% to -12% | 0 new entries | 0.0x | 0.0% | HALT + manual review required to resume |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Continuous monitoring of peak-to-trough equity drawdown.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Automatic scaling of position count, size, and heat as drawdown deepens. Recovery requires returning to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the previous level
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s threshold before privileges are restored (hysteresis prevents oscillation at boundaries).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Graduated response preserves capital during adverse sequences while avoiding the binary 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all-on/all-off
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: problem. Academic basis: Grossman 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhou (1993), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Optimal Investment Strategies for Controlling Drawdowns
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  —
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optimal drawdown control requires dynamic position reduction, not binary stops.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-05: DynamicSizer — 8-Factor Kelly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The DynamicSizer computes position size as a fraction of Kelly optimal, adjusted by 8 independent factors:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Factor | Description | Range |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|-------------|-------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 1. Win Rate | Rolling 50-trade win rate | 0.3-0.7 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 2.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Payoff Ratio | Average win / average loss | 0.5-3.0 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 3. Regime | Current HMM regime state | 0.5-1.0 multiplier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 4.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Drawdown Level | Current cascade level from R-04 | 0.0-1.0 multiplier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 5. Volatility Regime | ATR relative to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 60-day mean | 0.5-1.2 multiplier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 6. Correlation Load | Current portfolio correlation | 0.5-1.0 multiplier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 7. Signal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Confidence | Meta-model confidence score | 0.6-1.0 multiplier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 8. Liquidity Factor | Q/V ratio from Kyle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Lambda
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 0.5-1.0 multiplier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Formula
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: size = half_kelly(WR, PR) × Π(factor_multipliers) × equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Half-Kelly is used as the base (not full Kelly) to reduce variance of returns by 75% while sacrificing only ~25% of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: growth rate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Computed fresh for every trade entry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Final position size is the minimum of: DynamicSizer output, R-02 max risk (0.75%), and liquidity cap from
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-11/Section 7.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Multi-factor Kelly adapts to changing market conditions rather than using static sizing. Academic basis:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kelly (1956); Thorp (2006), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Kelly Criterion in Blackjack, Sports Betting, and the Stock Market
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — half-Kelly as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: practical optimum; MacLean, Thorp 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Ziemba (2011), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Good and Bad Properties of the Kelly Criterion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: New Controls (Added in v12.0-v13.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-06: Portfolio-Level Correlation Brake (Gate #34)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Ledoit-Wolf shrinkage covariance matrix computed on rolling 60-day returns for all held positions. If 3 or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more pairwise correlations exceed 0.70, the brake engages.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Cap concurrent positions at 1. No new entries until correlation subsides below 0.60 (hysteresis band of 0.10
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to prevent flicker). Existing positions are NOT force-closed — they retain their stops and profit targets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Leveraged ETPs on the same underlying (e.g., QQQ3.L and NVD3.L during a tech rally) create hidden
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: concentration risk. Nominal 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: diversification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  across 3 tickers that all track Nasdaq is an illusion. The Ledoit-Wolf
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrinkage estimator (2004) provides a well-conditioned covariance matrix even with limited samples, avoiding the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: estimation error that plagues raw sample covariance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Ledoit 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Wolf (2004), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A Well-Conditioned Estimator for Large-Dimensional Covariance Matrices
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; Kritzman, Page 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Turkington (2010), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In Defense of Optimization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — correlation-aware position limits.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-07: Portfolio CVaR + CDaR Gate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Two independent checks:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Per-trade CVaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Conditional Value-at-Risk at 95% confidence computed via historical simulation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on 252-day rolling returns. If single-trade CVaR exceeds 1.5% of equity → VETO.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Portfolio CDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Conditional Drawdown-at-Risk at 95% confidence for the aggregate portfolio. If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: portfolio CDaR exceeds 8% → HALT new entries.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : CVaR breach → individual trade vetoed. CDaR breach → all new entries halted until portfolio CDaR drops below
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6% (hysteresis).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : VaR is insufficient for fat-tailed leveraged ETP returns. CVaR (Expected Shortfall) captures tail risk that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VaR ignores. CDaR extends this to drawdown paths, which is the risk measure that actually matters for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compounding strategies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Rockafellar 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Uryasev (2000), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Optimization of Conditional Value-at-Risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; Chekhlov, Uryasev 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Zabarankin (2005), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Drawdown Measure in Portfolio Optimization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — CDaR as a coherent risk measure for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: path-dependent strategies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-08: Incremental CVaR (iCVaR) Veto
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Before any new position is added, compute the marginal increase in portfolio CVaR that the new position
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would cause. If iCVaR > 0.5% of equity → VETO.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Trade is vetoed with Telegram P1 notification: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iCVaR VETO: adding 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TICKER
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  would increase portfolio
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tail risk by 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: X
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: % (limit 0.5%).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : A position may look safe in isolation (passes R-07 per-trade CVaR) but could increase portfolio tail risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: disproportionately due to correlation or concentration effects. Incremental CVaR captures the marginal contribution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to total tail risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Tasche (2002), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expected Shortfall and Beyond
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — decomposition of ES into marginal contributions;
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rosen 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Saunders (2010), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Risk Factor Contributions in Portfolio Credit Risk Models
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — iCVaR methodology.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-09: Regime Transition Confirmation Buffer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : HMM regime model outputs a regime change (e.g., Bullish → Cautious, or Cautious → Crisis).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The regime change is NOT acted upon immediately. Instead, a 3-tick (3-minute) confirmation buffer is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: imposed. The new regime must persist for 3 consecutive ticks before any downstream parameters (sizing, heat caps,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: strategy activation) are updated. If the regime flips back within the buffer window, the transition is discarded as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: noise.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : HMM regime models are prone to flickering at regime boundaries, especially during choppy markets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Acting on every transition causes whipsawing — reducing size at exactly the wrong time, or increasing it prematurely.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 3-tick buffer filters false transitions at minimal cost (3 minutes of delayed response is acceptable given position
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: holding periods of hours to days).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Hamilton (1989), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A New Approach to the Economic Analysis of Nonstationary Time Series
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  —
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: original Markov switching model; Ang 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Bekaert (2002), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regime Switches in Interest Rates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — regime persistence as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a filtering mechanism.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-10: Anti-Correlation-Cascade Stop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 3 or more stop-outs occur within any rolling 15-minute window across all held positions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Immediate P0 HALT. All open orders are cancelled. No new entries for 30 minutes. Telegram P0 alert with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sound: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CASCADE DETECTED: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: N
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  stops in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: M
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  minutes. 30-min cool-down active.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Multiple simultaneous stop-outs indicate a correlated market shock (flash crash, news event, liquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vacuum). Continuing to trade during such events is extremely dangerous — spreads widen, fills deteriorate, and the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: next entry is likely to be stopped out as well. The 30-minute cool-down allows the market to find a new equilibrium.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Cont (2001), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Empirical Properties of Asset Returns: Stylized Facts and Statistical Issues
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — volatility
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clustering and contagion; Brunnermeier 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Pedersen (2009), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Market Liquidity and Funding Liquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — liquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spirals and cascade mechanics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-11: Market Maker Spread Veto
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Current bid-ask spread exceeds 2.5x the median spread over the previous 3 trading days.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Trade entry is VETOED. Re-check every tick (60 seconds). If spread normalises within the signal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s validity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: window, the trade may proceed. If not, the signal expires.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Abnormal spread widening signals either toxic order flow (informed traders), low liquidity, or market
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stress — all conditions where execution quality will be poor. Entering during wide spreads means paying excessive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: implicit costs that erode the 2% daily target.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Kyle (1985), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Continuous Auctions and Insider Trading
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — adverse selection and spread dynamics;
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Glosten 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Milgrom (1985), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Bid, Ask and Transaction Prices
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — spread as information cost.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-12: OBI Toxicity Wait Gate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Order Book Imbalance (OBI) exceeds 0.80 (i.e., >80% of visible depth is on one side of the book).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Wait 2 ticks (2 minutes), then re-check OBI. If OBI has normalised below 0.70, proceed with entry. If OBI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remains elevated, wait another 2 ticks (max 3 retries = 6 minutes total). After 3 retries, VETO the trade.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Extreme order book imbalance in low-volume ETPs often precedes a rapid price move in the opposite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: direction (spoofing, iceberg orders, or genuine informed flow). Waiting 2 minutes allows the imbalance to either
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: resolve (safe to enter) or materialise into the adverse move (bullet dodged).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Cont, Stoikov 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Talreja (2010), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A Stochastic Model for Order Book Dynamics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — OBI as predictor of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: short-term price direction; Cao, Chen 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Griffin (2005), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Informational Content of an Open Limit-Order Book
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-13: US Open Stop Widening
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Clock-based. Active between 14:30 and 15:30 UK time (US market open window).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : ATR multiplier for stop-loss placement is widened from 1.5x to 2.0x for any position entered or held during
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this window. This applies to both new entries and existing positions that have not yet reached Rung 1 of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Chandelier exit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The US market open (14:30 UK) creates a volatility spike in LSE-listed ETPs that track US indices.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: QQQ3.L, 3LUS.L, and similar instruments experience 2-3x normal volatility in the first 30-60 minutes as the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: underlying catches up to US pre-market moves. Using normal stop widths during this window results in excessive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stop-outs on noise.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Andersen 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Bollerslev (1997), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Intraday Periodicity and Volatility Persistence in Financial Markets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — U-shaped intraday volatility with spikes at market open; Harris (1986), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A Transaction Data Study of Weekly and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Intradaily Patterns in Stock Returns
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gemini R2 addition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : This control also addresses the LSE/NYSE Stampede Risk. At 14:30:01, the system imposes a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 60-second Gap-Stabilization wait before acting on any signal that requires LSE price data, preventing stale-price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entries during the cross-market synchronisation window.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-14: ETP Financing Cost Offset
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Any position held in an inverse or leveraged ETP for more than 1 trading day.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Subtract a daily financing drag from expected return calculations:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Long leveraged ETPs (e.g., QQQ3.L, 3LUS.L)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : -2 bps/day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Inverse leveraged ETPs (e.g., QQQS.L, 3USS.L)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : -4 bps/day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This drag is applied in the PnL tracking, signal scoring, and target price calculations. A 2% target on an inverse ETP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is therefore internally computed as a 2.04% gross target.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Leveraged and inverse ETPs carry daily financing costs (swap fees, roll costs, compounding drag) that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are invisible in the price but real in returns. Inverse ETPs carry roughly double the drag of long ETPs due to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: additional cost of maintaining short swap positions. Ignoring this drag over multi-day holds leads to systematic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: under-performance versus backtested expectations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Avellaneda 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zhang (2010), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Path-Dependence of Leveraged ETF Returns
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — compounding drag and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: financing cost analysis; Cheng 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Madhavan (2009), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Dynamics of Leveraged and Inverse Exchange-Traded
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Funds
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-15: Gamma/Strike Proximity Risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The underlying index or stock is within 0.5% of a major options strike price with significant open interest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (top 5 strikes by OI for the nearest monthly expiry).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Subtract 10 points from the signal confidence score. If confidence after subtraction falls below the minimum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entry threshold (60), the trade is vetoed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Options market makers who are short gamma near major strikes must delta-hedge aggressively, creating
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: artificial support/resistance and erratic price behaviour. Leveraged ETPs amplify this effect 3x. Entering a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: momentum trade near a pinning strike increases the probability of mean-reversion whipsaws.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Academic cite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Ni, Pearson 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Poteshman (2005), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stock Price Clustering on Option Expiration Dates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — options
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pinning effect; Avellaneda 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Lipkin (2003), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A Market-Induced Mechanism for Stock Pinning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — gamma exposure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and delta-hedging flows.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Drawdown Recovery Scaling by AUM
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: As equity grows, drawdown tolerance must tighten. A 12% drawdown on £10K is a £1,200 lesson. A 12% drawdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on £1M is a £120,000 catastrophe that takes months to recover from due to the compounding mathematics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | AUM Tier | Yellow | Orange | Red | Critical | Emergency |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
