   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | £10K -
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £100K | -2% | -4% | -8% | -10% | -12% |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | £100K - £500K | -1.5% | -3% | -6% | -8% | -10% |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | £500K - £1M | -1% | -2.5% |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -5% | -7% | -9% |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | £1M+ | -1% | -2% | -4% | -6% | -8% |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implementation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The drawdown cascade thresholds in R-04 are parameterised by 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: aum_tier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config/settings.yaml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . The tier is recalculated at the start of each trading day based on previous close equity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Transitions between tiers use the higher (tighter) thresholds — there is no grace period when crossing an AUM
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: boundary upward.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The Kelly criterion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,685:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s optimal bet size decreases as a fraction of bankroll when the cost of ruin increases.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: At £1M+, the system has proven its edge and the priority shifts from growth to capital preservation. Academic basis:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MacLean, Thorp 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Ziemba (2010), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Long-Term Capital Growth: The Good and Bad Properties of the Kelly and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fractional Kelly Capital Growth Criteria
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Control Interaction Matrix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No control operates in isolation. Key interactions:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-01 (Circuit Breakers) + R-04 (Cascade)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Circuit breakers trigger immediate halts; the cascade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: provides graduated response before the breaker trips. They are complementary, not redundant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-06 (Correlation Brake) + R-08 (iCVaR)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : R-06 uses pairwise correlation as a fast heuristic; R-08
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uses full portfolio tail risk as the precise measure. R-06 fires first (cheaper to compute), R-08 is the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: authoritative gate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-10 (Cascade Stop) + R-13 (US Open Widening)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : R-13 prevents unnecessary stop-outs during
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: US open volatility, which in turn prevents R-10 from triggering false cascade halts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-11 (Spread Veto) + R-12 (OBI Wait)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Both address microstructure risk but from different
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: angles. A trade must pass BOTH gates — wide spread vetoes immediately; normal spread but toxic OBI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: triggers a wait.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-07 (CVaR Gate) + R-08 (iCVaR)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : R-07 checks absolute tail risk per-trade and portfolio-wide.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: R-08 checks the marginal contribution. A trade can pass R-07 but fail R-08 if the portfolio is already
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loaded with correlated tail risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SECTION 7: LIQUIDITY SCALING MODEL
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Fundamental Constraint
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 2% daily compounding strategy is not constrained by signal quality, strategy logic, or infrastructure at small
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: equity sizes. The binding constraint at scale is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: liquidity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . LSE-listed leveraged ETPs are niche instruments with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: limited daily volume. The strategy must acknowledge this ceiling and plan for it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kyle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Lambda — Market Impact Model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The expected market impact of an order of size Q in a market with daily volume V is:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ΔP ≈ λ × √(Q / V_daily)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ΔP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = expected price impact (in basis points)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: λ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = Kyle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s lambda (market impact coefficient), empirically 0.1-0.3 for small-cap ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = order size in currency units
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: V_daily
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = average daily volume in currency units (ADV)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Reference
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Kyle (1985), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Continuous Auctions and Insider Trading
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — the foundational model of price impact as a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: function of order flow.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For NZT-48
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s instruments, we use λ = 0.20 (mid-range, conservative for leveraged ETPs which have wider spreads
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and thinner books than their underlying).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact Table — QQQ3.L Benchmark
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: QQQ3.L
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 57,000 shares/day average volume x ~£25/share = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £1,425,000 ADV
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Portfolio heat is capped at 3% (NOT 15% — corrected from Gemini R2 assumption). However, this table shows both
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the actual 3% heat and a theoretical 15% heat for comparison, because the liquidity model must be tested against
