   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Any external webhook or monitoring that references the IP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SSH connection commands in documentation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AWS Console → EC2 → Elastic IPs → Allocate Elastic IP address
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Associate to instance 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i-027add7c7366d4c86
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Update all references: deploy scripts, .env.production CORS, MEMORY.md
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cost: Free while instance is running. $0.005/hour if instance is stopped.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Priority
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : P0. This is a ticking time bomb — the next accidental stop/start will break the system until manually fixed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-02: Automate S3 Backup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scripts/backup_to_s3.sh
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  exists but is not scheduled. Backups only happen when manually
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remembered.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Add to crontab on EC2 instance (inside Docker or host)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Daily at 05:00 UTC (before London market open)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0 5 * * * /home/ubuntu/nzt48-signals/scripts/backup_to_s3.sh >>
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: /var/log/nzt48-backup.log 2>&1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Backup should include:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 1. SQLite database (full copy, not just WAL)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 2. Redis AOF dump
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 3. config/settings.yaml (in case of drift)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 4. Outcome/trade logs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Add backup verification:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # After upload, check S3 object exists and size > 0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Send Telegram P2 notification on success
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Send Telegram P0 notification on failure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Retention
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Keep 30 daily backups, 12 weekly backups (Sunday), 6 monthly backups. S3 Lifecycle policy handles
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rotation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-03: Fix VIX Default Value
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : When VIX data is unavailable (API failure, weekend, etc.), the system falls back to a static default of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 25.0. This is problematic because:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In calm markets (VIX 12-15), a default of 25 triggers false 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: elevated volatility
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  caution, causing the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system to reduce sizing and miss opportunities.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In crisis markets (VIX 40+), a default of 25 understates risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Gemini R2 ACCEPTED):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: def get_vix_default():
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Dynamic VIX default: max of last known VIX and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     20-day MA + 5.0 buffer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Falls back to static 20.0 only if no historical data exists.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     vix_last = get_last_known_vix()        # From Redis cache
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     vix_ma20 = get_vix_moving_average(20)  # From SQLite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     if vix_last and vix_ma20:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return max(vix_last, vix_ma20 + 5.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     elif vix_last:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return vix_last + 5.0  # Buffer for staleness
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     elif vix_ma20:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return vix_ma20 + 5.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     else:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         return 20.0  # Nuclear fallback (no data at all)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rationale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The dynamic default tracks the market
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s actual volatility regime rather than imposing a static assumption.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The +5.0 buffer on MA provides conservative bias when data is stale. Static 20.0 nuclear fallback is more neutral
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: than 25.0.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-04: Redis WAIT for State Persistence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Gemini R2 NEW): Race condition between Chandelier exit rung triggers and Redis persistence.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sequence:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Price hits Rung 2 → system writes new stop level to Redis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Docker restarts (update, OOM, crash) before Redis flushes to AOF
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: On restart, Redis loads stale state → stop level reverts to Rung 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position held with wrong (too loose) stop → excess risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: import redis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: def persist_critical_state(r: redis.Redis, key: str, value: str):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Write critical trading state to Redis with synchronous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: persistence.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Uses WAIT to ensure at least 0 replicas have acknowledged
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (which forces AOF flush on standalone Redis).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     """
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     pipe = r.pipeline()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     pipe.set(key, value)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     pipe.execute()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     # Force AOF rewrite if using AOF persistence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     r.bgsave()  # Or r.bgrewriteaof() depending on persistence mode
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     # For critical state, also write to SQLite as backup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     write_state_to_sqlite(key, value)  # Belt and braces
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Additional safeguard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : On Docker restart, the system compares Redis state against SQLite state. If they diverge,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SQLite wins (it uses WAL mode with synchronous writes). Telegram P0 alert is sent: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STATE DIVERGENCE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DETECTED: Redis key 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: X
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  differs from SQLite. SQLite value used.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Short-Term: Weeks 1-2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-05: Upgrade to t3.medium
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : t3.small has 2GB RAM. Current memory usage:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Python main process: ~800MB
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:45,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Redis: 256MB (will be 512MB after I-07)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Docker overhead: ~200MB
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SQLite page cache: ~100MB
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Total: ~1.35GB → leaving only 650MB headroom
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: With Apex Scout module running ML inference, memory spikes to ~1.8GB, leaving only 200MB before OOM
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: killer intervenes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Upgrade to t3.medium (2 vCPU, 4GB RAM). Same CPU, double the RAM.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Procedure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stop instance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Change instance type: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: aws ec2 modify-instance-attribute --instance-id
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i-027add7c7366d4c86 --instance-type t3.medium
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Start instance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Elastic IP re-associates automatically (if I-01 is done first)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cost increase: ~$0.0208/hr → ~$0.0416/hr (~$15/month increase)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Timing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Do this on a weekend when markets are closed. Total downtime: ~5 minutes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-06: CloudWatch Monitoring
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : The only monitoring is Telegram alerts for trading events. No visibility into infrastructure health: CPU
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: usage, memory pressure, disk space, Redis memory, SQLite size, process crashes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Deploy CloudWatch agent with custom metrics:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Metric | Source | Alarm Threshold | Action |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|--------|-----------------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | CPU Utilization | CloudWatch
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: built-in | > 80% for 5 min | P1 Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Memory Used % | CloudWatch agent | > 85% | P0 Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Disk Used
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: % | CloudWatch agent | > 80% | P1 Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Redis Memory | Custom metric (redis-cli INFO) | > 400MB | P1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | SQLite DB Size | Custom metric (ls -la) | > 500MB | P2 Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Signals/Hour | Custom metric (app
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: log parsing) | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 during market hours | P1 Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Docker Container Restarts | Custom metric (docker inspect) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: > 0 in 1 hour | P0 Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Backup Age | Custom metric (S3 last modified) | > 26 hours | P0 Telegram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cost
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : CloudWatch agent is free. Custom metrics: $0.30/metric/month x 8 = $2.40/month.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-07: Redis Memory Limit 256 -> 512MB
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : As the number of tracked instruments grows and Chandelier exit state accumulates, Redis memory usage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will approach the 256MB limit. When Redis hits its memory limit with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maxmemory-policy noeviction
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: writes fail silently, causing state corruption.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Update 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker-compose.yml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nzt48-redis:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   image: redis:7-alpine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   command: redis-server --requirepass nzt48redis --maxmemory 512mb
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: --maxmemory-policy noeviction --appendonly yes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rebuild: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose up -d nzt48-redis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Medium-Term: Month 2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-08: PostgreSQL Migration (RDS)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : SQLite is excellent for the current scale but has fundamental limitations:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Single-writer: concurrent writes from the web API and the engine can cause SQLITE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BUSY errors
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No replication: single point of failure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Backup requires file-level copy (cannot do hot logical backups)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No connection pooling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 22 tables will grow; query performance on large tables degrades without proper indexing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Migrate to AWS RDS PostgreSQL (db.t3.micro, ~$15/month).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Migration plan
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Schema conversion: SQLite → PostgreSQL DDL (mostly compatible, fix AUTOINCREMENT →
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SERIAL, datetime handling)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Data migration: pgloader for one-shot migration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Application changes: Switch SQLAlchemy engine URI from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sqlite:///
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: postgresql://
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Test in parallel: Run both databases for 1 week, compare state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cutover: Point application to RDS, keep SQLite as read-only backup for 1 month
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Benefit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Enables future multi-process architecture (separate API server, separate engine, separate ML worker) all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sharing the same database.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I-09: CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Every deployment is a manual SSH + docker build process. This is error-prone and creates anxiety around
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: deploying changes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fix
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : GitHub Actions workflow:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # .github/workflows/deploy.yml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: name: Deploy to EC2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   push:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     branches: [main]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: jobs:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   test:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     steps:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - run: pip install -r requirements.txt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - run: python -m pytest tests/ -v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   deploy:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     needs: test
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     steps:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       - name: Deploy to EC2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         uses: appleboy/ssh-action@v1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         with:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           host: ${{ secrets.EC2_HOST }}  # Elastic IP from I-01
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           username: ubuntu
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           key: ${{ secrets.EC2_SSH_KEY }}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           script: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             cd /home/ubuntu/nzt48-signals
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             git pull origin main
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             docker compose build nzt48
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             docker compose up -d nzt48
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Deployment only proceeds if all tests pass. Failed tests block the deploy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Notification Architecture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Priority Levels
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Priority | Use Case | Delivery | Rate Limit | Sound |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
