   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ## SECTION 11: MATHEMATICAL APPENDIX
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ### §11.1 Bayesian Stranger Penalty (Shrinkage Model)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The **Stranger Penalty** implements empirical Bayesian shrinkage to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: prevent overfitting to spurious edge signals in strategies with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: insufficient trade history. The penalty coefficient κ ∈ [0.25, 1.0]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: multiplicatively scales the raw confidence signal, with full trust
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (κ=1.0) granted only after statistical graduation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Primary Shrinkage Formula:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: κ(n, DSR) = κ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: min + (κ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max - κ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: min) × f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR(DSR) × f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n(n)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `κ_min = 0.25` — maximum distrust (new/unproven strategies)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `κ_max = 1.0` — full trust (graduated strategies)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `n` — number of closed trades for the strategy-ticker-leverage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: combination
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `DSR` — Deflated Sharpe Ratio (Bailey & López de Prado 2012)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Component Functions:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR(DSR) = 1 - exp(-λ × max(0, DSR - DSR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: min))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n(n) = n / (n + n₀)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Parameters (v13.0 calibration):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `λ = 0.5` (changed from v12's 0.8) — decay rate for DSR sensitivity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `DSR_min = 1.5` — minimum threshold for risk-adjusted performance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `n₀ = 50` (changed from v12's 30) — half-life for sample size
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discounting
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Deflated Sharpe Ratio Computation:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The DSR adjusts the observed Sharpe Ratio for multiple testing and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: non-normality:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DSR = (SR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: observed - SR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: benchmark) / SE(SR)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: observed = (μ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: returns - r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f) / σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: returns
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: benchmark = √(2 ln(N
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tests))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SE(SR) = √
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (1 + (SR²/2) - γ₁ × SR + (γ₂ - 1)/4 × SR²) / (n - 1)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `μ_returns` — mean per-trade return
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `r_f` — risk-free rate (assumed 0 for intraday signals)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `σ_returns` — standard deviation of returns
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `N_tests` — number of strategy configurations tested
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (conservatively set to 150 for 15 strategies × 10 parameter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: variants)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `γ₁` — sample skewness
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `γ₂` — sample excess kurtosis
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `n` — number of trades
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Graduation Threshold (Harvey, Liu & Zhu 2016):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A strategy graduates from the penalty when its t-statistic exceeds
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the multiple-testing threshold:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stat = SR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: observed × √n ≥ 3.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: At graduation, κ is frozen at 1.0 regardless of future DSR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fluctuations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Bayesian Prior (v13.0 addition):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: To complement frequentist graduation, we impose a Bayesian prior on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: edge existence:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: μ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: edge ~ Normal(0, 0.5%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: edge ~ Inv-Gamma(shape=3, scale=0.1)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Graduation requires:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: P(Sharpe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: annual > 1.5 | data) > 0.98
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This dual-gate approach (t-stat ≥ 3.0 AND Bayesian posterior
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: probability > 0.98) provides robust protection against Type I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: errors while allowing genuine alpha to graduate within 60-100
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trades.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Example Progression:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | n    | DSR  | f_n(n) | f_DSR | κ     | Status      |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|------|--------|-------|-------|-------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 10   | 1.2  | 0.17   | 0.00  | 0.25  | Stranger    |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 30   | 2.0  | 0.38   | 0.31  | 0.34  | Probation   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 60   | 2.5  | 0.55   | 0.53  | 0.47  | Maturing    |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 90   | 2.8  | 0.64   | 0.63  | 0.56  | Near-grad   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 120  | 3.1  | 0.71   | 0.69  | 0.62  | **Graduated** (t=5.4) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 120+ | any  | -      | -     | 1.00  | Full trust  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ---
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ### §11.2 Stoikov OBI-Adjusted Entry Price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The **Stoikov Entry Price Model** adapts market microstructure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: theory (Stoikov & Waeber 2016) to adjust limit order placement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: based on order book imbalance (OBI) and urgency, explicitly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: accounting for leverage amplification of adverse selection risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Primary Formula:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ŝ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L = s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mid + L × β
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI × OBI × σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1min × urgency(t)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `ŝ_L` — optimal limit price for leverage level L
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `s_mid` — current mid-price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `L` — leverage factor {1, 2, 3, 5}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `β_OBI` — leverage-dependent OBI sensitivity coefficient
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `OBI` — order book imbalance ∈ [-1, +1]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `σ_1min` — 1-minute realized volatility (Yang-Zhang estimator)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `urgency(t)` — time-to-close urgency multiplier
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Leverage-Continuous OBI Coefficient (v13.0):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: β
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI = 0.5 × L^1.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This continuous power-law formulation replaces v12's discrete
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lookup table, capturing the super-linear scaling of adverse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: selection risk with leverage. The exponent 1.2 reflects empirical
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: observation that market impact compounds non-linearly in leveraged
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ETPs due to:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Larger notional size per pound of risk capital
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Wider bid-ask spreads in leveraged instruments
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Shallower order books at higher multiples
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Discrete Values:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - L=1: β_OBI = 0.50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - L=2: β_OBI = 1.15
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - L=3: β_OBI = 1.93
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - L=5: β_OBI = 3.47
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Order Book Imbalance:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI = (V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bid - V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ask) / (V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bid + V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ask)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where V_bid and V_ask are cumulative volumes within 20bps of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mid-price.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Urgency Function (v13.0 singularity fix):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The urgency multiplier increases as market close approaches,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: creating a logarithmic incentive to fill orders before EOD:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: urgency(t) = min(ln(T / (T - t)), ln(T / 5))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `T` — total trading window in minutes (510 for UK ISA: 8:00-16:30)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `t` — current elapsed minutes since market open
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The `min()` operator **caps urgency at the T-5min value**,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: preventing the singularity that occurred in v12 when (T-t) → 0. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ensures bounded urgency even if signals fire within the final 5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: minutes of trading.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Expected Value Gate:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Before submitting a limit order, we compute the net expected return
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: after adverse selection and slippage:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: net
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expected
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: return = μ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signal - |ŝ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L - s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mid| - spread/2 - stop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: distance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VETO if: net
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expected
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: return 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1.5 × stop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: distance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This ensures that OBI-induced skew does not erode edge to the point
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where the trade becomes marginally unprofitable even before price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: movement.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Example Calculation:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Given:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L = 3 (3x leveraged ETP)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mid = £10.50
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI = +0.35 (bid-heavy, bullish signal)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1min = £0.04
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t = 420 min (90 min to close)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: T = 510 min
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compute:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: β
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI = 0.5 × 3^1.2 = 1.93
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: urgency = ln(510 / (510-420)) = ln(5.67) = 1.735
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ŝ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3 = 10.50 + 3 × 1.93 × 0.35 × 0.04 × 1.735
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ŝ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3 = 10.50 + 0.141 = £10.641
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Interpretation: Place buy limit at £10.64 (14.1p above mid) to balance fill probability and adverse selection risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ---
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ### §11.3 Portfolio CVaR + CDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Conditional Value at Risk (CVaR)** and **Conditional Drawdown at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Risk (CDaR)** quantify tail risk at the per-trade and portfolio
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: levels respectively, providing complementary veto gates that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: prevent catastrophic losses while allowing normal volatility to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: breathe.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **§11.3.1 Conditional Value at Risk (Per-Trade Gate)**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CVaR measures the expected loss in the worst α% of outcomes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CVaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α = E
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Loss | Loss > VaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α = inf{x : P(Loss ≤ x) ≥ α}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For α = 0.95 (95th percentile), CVaR₀.₉₅ is the mean loss conditional on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: being in the worst 5% of historical outcomes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Empirical Estimation (Rockafellar & Uryasev 2000):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Given N historical trade outcomes {r₁, r₂, ..., rₙ} sorted ascending:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: k = ⌈α × N⌉
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α ≈ r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: k
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CVaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α ≈ (1 / (N × (1-α))) × Σ(i=k to N) max(0, -r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Gate Threshold:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VETO if: CVaR₀.₉₅ > 3% of equity per trade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This per-trade gate prevents individual positions from carrying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: unacceptable tail risk, regardless of portfolio composition. The 3%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold reflects maximum tolerable single-trade loss at the 95th
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: percentile, consistent with 1% mean risk budget and 3:1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tail-to-mean ratio.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:46,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **§11.3.2 Conditional Drawdown at Risk (Portfolio-Level Breaker)**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CDaR extends CVaR to path-dependent drawdown risk, capturing serial
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: correlation and portfolio heat accumulation (Chekhlov, Uryasev &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Zabarankin 2005):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Drawdown(t) = max(W
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: peak - W
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t, 0) / W
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: peak
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α = inf{x : P(Drawdown ≤ x) ≥ α}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α = E
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Drawdown | Drawdown > DDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Portfolio Breaker:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HALT all new entries if: CDaR₀.₉₅ > 5% of equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RESUME when: CDaR₀.₉₅ 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 3% hysteresis band (5% halt, 2% resume) prevents thrashing at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the boundary. This portfolio-level circuit breaker complements
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: per-trade CVaR by capturing correlated losses across simultaneous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: positions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **§11.3.3 Incremental CVaR (Admission Veto)**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Before admitting a new position, we compute the marginal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: contribution to portfolio tail risk:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iCVaR = CVaR(portfolio + new position) - CVaR(portfolio)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where CVaR is computed on the joint distribution of returns using
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1000-sample bootstrap from Ledoit-Wolf shrunken covariance matrix.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Gate:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VETO if: iCVaR > 0.5% of equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This ensures that no single admission degrades portfolio tail risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by more than 50bps, enforcing diversification at the marginal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: level.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Example:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Portfolio state:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position 1: QQQ3.L, £300, CVaR = 2.1%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position 2: 3LUS.L, £250, CVaR = 1.9%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Portfolio CVaR = 2.8% (sub-additive due to ρ = 0.82)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: New candidate:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position 3: TSL3.L, £200, CVaR = 2.5%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Joint CVaR = 3.2%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iCVaR = 3.2% - 2.8% = 0.4% 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0.5% → ADMIT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Summary Table:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Metric        | Level      | Threshold        | Action          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Purpose                     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------------|------------|------------------|-----------------|-----------------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | CVaR₀.₉₅      | Per-trade  | > 3% equity      | Veto entry      |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Prevent single-trade ruin   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | CDaR₀.₉₅      | Portfolio  | > 5% equity      | Halt all trades |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Circuit breaker             |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | CDaR₀.₉₅      | Portfolio  | < 2% equity      | Resume trading  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hysteresis band             |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | iCVaR         | Marginal   | > 0.5% equity    | Veto admission  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Preserve diversification    |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ---
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ### §11.4 Amihud Illiquidity with Leverage Exponent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The **Amihud Illiquidity Ratio** (Amihud 2002) quantifies price
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: impact per unit volume, extended to account for leverage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amplification and intraday volume patterns specific to UK ISA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trading hours.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Primary Formula:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ILLIQ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i = (1/D) × Σ(d=1 to D) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d| / V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  × L^α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `D` — lookback window (20 trading days)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `r_d` — daily return on day d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `V_d` — daily volume in GBP on day d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `L` — leverage factor {1, 2, 3, 5}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `α` — leverage exponent (empirically calibrated)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Leverage Exponent α (v13.0 calibration):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Leverage | α Value | Reasoning                                    
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |----------|---------|------------------------------------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 1x       | 1.0     | Baseline (unleveraged instruments)          
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 2x       | 1.25    | Modest compounding of market impact         
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 3x       | 1.5     | Non-linear impact due to rebalancing flows  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 5x       | 2.0     | Quadratic impact from daily reset
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amplification|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The super-linear exponents (α > 1) for leveraged ETPs reflect:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. **Rebalancing flows**: Daily reset mechanics create predictable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: end-of-day order flow proportional to L×|Δ%|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. **Shallow books**: Market makers quote wider spreads and thinner
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: depth at higher leverage multiples
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. **Cascading liquidations**: Stop-losses cluster more densely in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leveraged products, creating feedback loops
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Intraday Volume Adjustment (UK ISA):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UK market volume follows a pronounced U-shaped intraday pattern. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: adjust effective volume by time-of-day:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: effective(t) = V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: observed × f(t)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f(t) = 1.25 - 0.25 × cos(2π(t - 9) / 8.5)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where `t` ∈ [8:00, 16:30] is UK market time. This sinusoidal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: approximation peaks at market open (f(8:00) = 1.50) and close
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (f(16:30) = 1.50), with a trough near midday (f(12:15) = 1.00).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Purge Threshold:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VETO if: heat
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: size × ILLIQ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i > 0.005
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where `heat_size` is the proposed position size in GBP. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold 0.005 implies that a £300 position (typical 3% heat) in an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: instrument with ILLIQ = 0.0167 would be at the boundary:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £300 × 0.0167 = 0.005 (boundary case)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This gate prevents entries where expected slippage + market impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would exceed 50bps of position value.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Example Calculation:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ticker: TSL3.L (3x leveraged Tesla)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Data (20-day window):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mean |r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d| = 3.2%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mean V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d = £450,000
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L = 3, α = 1.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Base illiquidity:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ILLIQ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: base = (1/20) × Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.2% / £450,000
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 0.0000071 × 20 = 0.000142
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Leverage-adjusted:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ILLIQ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TSL3 = 0.000142 × 3^1.5 = 0.000142 × 5.196 = 0.000738
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Check gate for £300 position:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heat
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: size × ILLIQ = £300 × 0.000738 = 0.221 >> 0.005 → PURGE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Conclusion: TSL3.L exhibits excessive illiquidity for £300 positions at current volumes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Comparison to Kyle's Lambda:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: While Kyle's Lambda (Kyle 1985) measures market depth λ = ΔP / ΔV
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: directly from order book snapshots, Amihud's ratio uses publicly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: available daily data, making it suitable for retail-scale systems
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: without L2 feed costs. The correlation between ILLIQ and λ is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: approximately 0.73 (Goyenko, Holden & Trzcinka 2009), sufficient
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for our purge gate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ---
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ### §11.5 Ledoit-Wolf Shrinkage Correlation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The **Ledoit-Wolf Covariance Shrinkage Estimator** (Ledoit & Wolf
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2004) provides a well-conditioned correlation matrix for portfolio
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk computation, essential when the number of assets approaches
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the number of observations (high-dimensional regime).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Problem Statement:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The sample covariance matrix Σ_sample is ill-conditioned when:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Number of assets p approaches number of observations n
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Extreme eigenvalues lead to unstable matrix inversion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Optimization algorithms diverge or produce corner solutions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Shrinkage Formula:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrunk = α × Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sample + (1 - α) × F
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `Σ_sample` — sample covariance matrix (p × p)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `F` — shrinkage target (structured estimator)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - `α ∈ [0, 1]` — shrinkage intensity (data-driven)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Shrinkage Target F (Single-Factor Model):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ij = β
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i × β
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: j × σ²
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: market    if i ≠ j
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ii = σ²
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i                      if i = j
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where β_i is the asset's market beta, estimated via OLS regression
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on FTSE 100 returns.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Optimal Shrinkage Intensity α:**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ledoit-Wolf provide an analytic formula for α that minimizes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expected quadratic loss:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = max(0, min(1, (κ - n²) / δ²))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: κ = (1/n²) × Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t ||r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  - Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sample||²
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: δ² = ||Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sample - F||²
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where ||·||_F denotes Frobenius norm and r_t is the vector of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: returns at time t.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: **Implementation (already in `uk_isa/correlation_engine.py`):**
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The NZT-48 codebase implements Ledoit-Wolf shrinkage via
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: `sklearn.covariance.LedoitWolf` with the following configuration:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ```python
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from sklearn.covariance import LedoitWolf
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: estimator = LedoitWolf(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     store_precision=True,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     assume_centered=False,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     block_size=1000
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Σ_shrunk = estimator.fit(returns_matrix).covariance_
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α_optimal = estimator.shrinkage_
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Typical Results (NZT-48 ISA universe, n=60 days, p=12 funds):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Scenario          | α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
