   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sample) | Condition Number (Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrunk) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------------------|------|-----------------------------|-----------------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Low correlation   | 0.18 | 23.4                      
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 8.1                         |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Medium correlation| 0.31 | 89.2                        | 12.6                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Crisis (ρ→1)      | 0.52 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 347.1                       | 18.3                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Usage in NZT-48:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Portfolio CVaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Joint tail risk computed via bootstrap sampling from N(0, Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrunk)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Incremental CVaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Marginal contributions use Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrunk to avoid spurious correlation artifacts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position sizing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Diversification credit δ = √(w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrunk w) / √(w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  diag(Σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shrunk) w)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theoretical Guarantee:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For p/n → c ∈ (0, 1), the Ledoit-Wolf estimator achieves:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E[||Σ_shrunk - Σ_true||²_F] = O(p/n)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compared to O(p) for the sample estimator, providing asymptotic consistency even in high-dimensional regimes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §11.6 PEAD Power-Law Decay
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Post-Earnings Announcement Drift (PEAD)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  exhibits predictable momentum following quarterly earnings
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: surprises (Bernard 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Thomas 1989). We model this drift as a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: power-law decay
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  rather than exponential, consistent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with empirical microstructure and information diffusion dynamics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Primary Model:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: residual(t) = α × (t + 1)^(-β)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: residual(t)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — expected abnormal return on day t post-earnings
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — days since earnings announcement (t ∈ 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0, 60
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α = 0.30
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — initial magnitude (30bps day-0 jump for 1-SD surprise)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: β = 0.5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — decay exponent (square-root law)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theoretical Justification:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The square-root decay (β = 0.5) aligns with:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kyle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Model (1985)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Informed traders
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  optimal strategy under sequential trading
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Information Diffusion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Power-law attention cascades in social networks (Bakshy et al. 2011)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Empirical Finance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Chordia, Subrahmanyam 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tong (2014) document t^(-0.48) decay in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: post-event momentum
