   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 20       | 6.5 bps                          | 4.1 bps                         | 1.59        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 40       | 4.7 bps                          | 0.7 bps        
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                 | 6.71        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 60       | 3.8 bps                          | 0.1 bps                         | 38.00       |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key Insight:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Power-law decay generates:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Faster initial drop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (days 0-5): More realistic fade of immediate over-reaction
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fatter tail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (days 20-60): Persistent drift consistent with slow information diffusion to retail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: investors
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exponential decay underestimates long-horizon effects, leading to premature signal termination.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Integration into S15 (Daily Target Strategy):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When an earnings announcement occurs for a constituent of a leveraged ETP (e.g., NVDA earnings → NVD3.L):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: boost_factor = Σ(i ∈ top_10_holdings) [w_i × sign(surprise_i) ×
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: residual(t_i)]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conf_adjusted = conf_base × (1 + boost_factor)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: w_i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — weight of security i in the ETP (typically 5-15% for top-10)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: surprise_i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — standardized earnings surprise (EPS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: actual - EPS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consensus) / σ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: forecast
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t_i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — days since security i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s earnings
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Example (NVD3.L on day 3 post-NVDA earnings):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Given:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - NVDA weight in NVD3.L: w = 0.12
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Earnings surprise: +2.1 SD (beat)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - t = 3 days post-announcement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compute:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - residual(3) = 0.30 × (3+1)^(-0.5) = 0.30 × 0.5 = 0.150 (15bps)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - boost = 0.12 × sign(+2.1) × 0.150 = +0.018 (+1.8%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - conf_adjusted = 0.65 × (1 + 0.018) = 0.662 (modest lift)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If combined with strong momentum + low volatility regime, this tips
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: S15 to trigger entry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Decay Horizon:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PEAD signal is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: purged after t > 60 days
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to prevent noise accumulation. Empirical studies (Chordia et al. 2014)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: show reversion to random walk by day 90, with our 60-day cutoff providing 2σ safety margin.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §11.7 Regime-Conditional Kelly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kelly Criterion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Kelly 1956) maximizes long-run geometric growth rate but requires regime-conditional
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scaling to prevent over-betting in adverse market environments. NZT-48 implements a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: seven-regime framework
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with empirically calibrated multipliers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard Kelly Formula:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f* = (p × b - q) / b
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f*
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — fraction of bankroll to wager
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: p
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — win probability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: q = 1 - p
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — loss probability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: b
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — odds received on a win (b = win
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: size / loss
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: size)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regime-Conditional Scaling:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_regime = f* × m_regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: REQUIRE: n_regime ≥ 30 trades
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ELSE: f_regime = f_global × 0.5 × m_regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m_regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is the regime-specific multiplier from the table below.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Seven-Regime Multiplier Table (v13.0):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Regime ID | Description            | Multiplier (m) | Rationale                                      |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-----------|------------------------|----------------|------------------------------------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
