   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regime Classification (HMM from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: core/cross_asset_macro.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regimes are detected via Hidden Markov Model with 7 latent states, trained on:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SPX returns (1d, 5d, 20d momentum)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VIX level + VIX term structure slope
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Credit spreads (HYG-IEF OAS)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fear 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Greed Index
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DXY (dollar strength)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Minimum Sample Requirement:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: To compute regime-specific Kelly, we require:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n_regime ≥ 30 closed trades in the current regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If insufficient history exists, fall back to:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_regime = f_global × 0.5 × m_regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_global
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is computed from all-regime pooled outcomes. The 0.5 deflator adds conservatism when
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime-specific statistics are unreliable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Example Calculation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strategy: S15 (Daily Target 2%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Global outcomes (N = 150 trades):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Wins: 95 (p = 0.63)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Losses: 55 (q = 0.37)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Avg win: +2.1%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - Avg loss: -1.0%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: - b = 2.1 / 1.0 = 2.1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard Kelly:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f* = (0.63 × 2.1 - 0.37) / 2.1 = (1.323 - 0.37) / 2.1 = 0.454
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (45.4%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regime: TRENDING_UP_STRONG (m = 0.60)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n_regime = 42 trades ≥ 30 → sufficient data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_regime = 0.454 × 0.60 = 0.272 (27.2%)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position size for £10,000 equity:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heat = £10,000 × 0.272 = £2,720
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: With 3x leverage:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: notional = £2,720 / 3 = £907 market exposure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric Mean Optimization:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Kelly fraction maximizes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G(f) = Σ(i=1 to N) p_i × ln(1 + f × r_i)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where r
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i are the outcome returns. The optimal f
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  satisfies:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dG/df = 0 = Σ(i=1 to N) [p_i × r_i / (1 + f* × r_i)]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For regime-conditional Kelly, we solve this equation independently for each regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s empirical return distribution,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: then apply the multiplier m
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: regime as a risk overlay.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Zero-Multiplier Regimes (RISK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OFF, SHOCK):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When m = 0.00, all position entry logic is suspended:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scout Radar continues (monitoring only)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Open positions remain subject to Chandelier exit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No new Gauntlet admissions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CDaR breaker automatically engaged
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hard halt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  prevents the classic Kelly failure mode where geometric ruin occurs from a single catastrophic loss
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: during a regime shift.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §11.8 Kelly Geometric Mean Optimization for Bank/Trail Split
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 33/67 bank-trail split
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (33% fixed bank target, 67% trailing stop via Chandelier) emerges from geometric mean
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optimization accounting for the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 40bps spread drag
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  inherent in dual-exit execution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Problem Setup:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A dual-exit strategy incurs:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1 entry spread (paid once)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2 exit spreads (bank leg + trail leg execute separately)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Total drag: 3 × (spread/2) ≈ 40bps for typical 27bp bid-ask on 3x ETPs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The question: what bank/trail split α/(1-α) maximizes long-run geometric growth after spread drag?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric Mean Objective:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G(α) = E[ln(1 + r_net)]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: r_net = α × r_bank + (1-α) × r_trail - drag
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — fraction of position targeting fixed bank profit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: r_bank
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — return if bank target hit (typically +2% for Rung 0, +4% for Rung 1, etc.)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: r_trail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — return if trail stop hit (varies by trade duration and volatility)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drag = 0.40%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — spread cost of dual exit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Monte Carlo Simulation (1,000,000 trades):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We simulated S15 (Daily Target) outcomes under historical vol/drift parameters, sweeping α ∈ 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0.25, 0.75
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in 5%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: increments:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Split (Bank/Trail) | Mean Return | Std Dev | Sharpe | Geometric Mean G(α) | Spread Drag Cost |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------------------|-------------|---------|--------|---------------------|------------------|
