   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 60% /
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 40%          | +1.64%      | 1.09%   | 1.50   | +0.978%             | -0.388%          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 75% / 25%          | +1.68%      | 1.08%  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 1.56   | +0.932%             | -0.382%          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key Findings:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Arithmetic mean increases monotonically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with bank allocation (more profit-taking → higher mean)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric mean peaks at 33/67
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  due to volatility drag offsetting the mean gain
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spread drag decreases
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with bank allocation (fewer trail-only exits), but the effect is minor (41bp →
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 38bp)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mathematical Intuition:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The geometric mean penalizes variance:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: G ≈ μ - σ²/2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ∂G/∂α = ∂μ/∂α - σ × ∂σ/∂α
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: At low α (e.g., 25/75):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trail-heavy → high variance from long-duration holds
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Volatility drag dominates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: At high α (e.g., 75/25):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Bank-heavy → leaves too much tail profit on table
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Arithmetic mean gain doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t offset geometric penalty
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: At α = 0.33:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Goldilocks zone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : captures early 2% moves (Rung 0) while letting 67% ride for outliers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trail component captures the 4-8% runners that drive compounding
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spread Drag Adjustment:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 40bp drag is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amortized
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  across both exit legs:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drag_per_trade = (bid_ask / 2) × 3 = 0.13% × 3 = 0.40%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: effective_return = gross_return - 0.40%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This cost is independent of bank/trail split (both legs pay spread), but the geometric mean G(α) is maximized when
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the split balances mean vs. variance optimally.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Robustness Check (Regime Breakdown):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Regime            | Optimal α | G(α) @ 33/67 | G(α) @ 50/50 | Δ Geometric |
