   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | How do we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reconcile the 2% Daily Target with the reality that compounding requires banking profits? What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the optimal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bank/trail split? | Geometric mean optimization after 40bps spread drag shows 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 33% bank / 67% trail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  maximizes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: long-run growth (G = +1.041% vs. +1.006% for 50/50). The 33% fraction captures early 2% Rung 0 moves while
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: letting 67% ride for 4-8% outliers. Spread drag is minor (41bp → 38bp across splits) but volatility penalty dominates at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extremes. Monte Carlo over 1M trades confirms robustness across regimes. | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §4.4
