   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Apex Scout scans 200-500 tickers. What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the data cost at scale? When
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: do we graduate from free yfinance to paid APIs? | yfinance is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: free and sufficient for £10K-£100K
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  equity. Pre-filter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 200-500 candidates on daily bars (free), then trigger 1-min scanning only for top 20-30 movers (still free, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 250
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: requests). At 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: £500K+ equity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , graduate to paid APIs (Polygon £200/mo, Alpha Vantage £500/mo) for millisecond-level
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L1 quotes. Phase 1-2 operate entirely on free yfinance with 60s scan loops. | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §3.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Apex Scout), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §3.3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Infrastructure) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | OBI coefficient β
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI has discrete values (1x=0.5, 2x=1.15, 3x=1.93, 5x=3.47). Is there a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: continuous formula or hierarchy principle? | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Continuous formula
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in v13.0: β
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OBI = 0.5 × L^1.2. The exponent 1.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reflects super-linear adverse selection scaling due to (1) larger notional per £ risk capital, (2) wider spreads in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leveraged ETPs, (3) shallower order books. This replaces the v12 lookup table and allows fractional leverage if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: future phases introduce dynamic de-levering. Hierarchy: β scales polynomially, not linearly. | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §4.3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Stoikov OBI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Entry), 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: §11.2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Mathematical Derivation) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q4
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | CVaR and CDaR both appear. Are they redundant? Which takes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: priority in a conflict? | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Not redundant
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . CVaR (per-trade, 3% gate) prevents individual position ruin. CDaR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (portfolio-level, 5% breaker with 2% re-entry hysteresis) prevents correlated drawdown spirals across simultaneous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: positions. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Priority
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : CDaR halt overrides all CVaR-passed entries (portfolio survival > individual opportunity).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Complementary: CVaR = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t enter this trade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , CDaR = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t enter ANY trade right now
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 16:39:47,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
